74// replaces { with < and } with > and also
75// replaces &gt; with < and &gt; with > within string s
76static void unescapeCRef(QCString &s)
77{
78 QCString result;
79 const char *p = s.data();
80 if (p)
81 {
82 char c;
83 while ((c=*p++))
84 {
85 if (c=='{') c='<'; else if (c=='}') c='>';
86 result+=c;
87 }
88 }
89
90 result=substitute(result,"&lt;","<");
91 result=substitute(result,"&gt;",">");
92 s = result;
93}

97/*! Strips known html and tex extensions from \a text. */
98static QCString stripKnownExtensions(const QCString &text)
99{
100 QCString result=text;
101 if (result.endsWith(".tex"))
102 {
103 result=result.left(result.length()-4);
104 }
105 else if (result.right(Doxygen::htmlFileExtension.length())==
106 QCString(Doxygen::htmlFileExtension))
107 {
108 result=result.left(result.length()-Doxygen::htmlFileExtension.length());
109 }
110 return result;
111}

115 std::visit([&](auto &&x)->decltype(auto) { return x.setParent(newParent); }, *n);

121{

152//----------- DocEmoji
153
154DocEmoji::DocEmoji(DocParser *parser,DocNodeVariant *parent,const QCString &symName) :
155 DocNode(parser,parent), m_symName(symName), m_index(-1)
156{
157 QCString locSymName = symName;
158 uint len=locSymName.length();
159 if (len>0)
160 {
161 if (locSymName.at(len-1)!=':') locSymName.append(":");
162 if (locSymName.at(0)!=':') locSymName.prepend(":");
163 }
164 m_symName = locSymName;
165 m_index = EmojiEntityMapper::instance().symbol2index(m_symName.str());
166 if (m_index==-1)
167 {
168 warn_doc_error(parser->context.fileName,parser->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"Found unsupported emoji symbol '%s'\n",qPrint(m_symName));
169 }
170}

203DocAnchor::DocAnchor(DocParser *parser,DocNodeVariant *parent,const QCString &id,bool newAnchor) : DocNode(parser,parent)
204{
205 if (id.isEmpty())
206 {
207 warn_doc_error(parser->context.fileName,parser->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"Empty anchor label");
208 return;
209 }
210
211 const CitationManager &ct = CitationManager::instance();
212 QCString anchorPrefix = ct.anchorPrefix();
213 if (id.left(anchorPrefix.length()) == anchorPrefix)
214 {
215 const CiteInfo *cite = ct.find(id.mid(anchorPrefix.length()));
216 if (cite)
217 {
218 m_file = convertNameToFile(ct.fileName(),FALSE,TRUE);
219 m_anchor = id;
220 }
221 else
222 {
223 warn_doc_error(parser->context.fileName,parser->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"Invalid cite anchor id '%s'",qPrint(id));
224 m_anchor = "invalid";
225 m_file = "invalid";
226 }
227 }
228 else if (newAnchor) // found <a name="label">
229 {
230 m_anchor = id;
231 }
232 else // found \anchor label
233 {
234 const SectionInfo *sec = SectionManager::instance().find(id);
235 if (sec)
236 {
237 //printf("Found anchor %s\n",qPrint(id));
238 m_file = sec->fileName();
239 m_anchor = sec->label();
240 }
241 else
242 {
243 warn_doc_error(parser->context.fileName,parser->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"Invalid anchor id '%s'",qPrint(id));
244 m_anchor = "invalid";
245 m_file = "invalid";
246 }
247 }
248}

261
262void DocInclude::parse(DocNodeVariant *)
263{
264 DBG(("DocInclude::parse(file=%s,text=%s)\n",qPrint(m_file),qPrint(m_text)));
265 switch(m_type)
266 {
267 case DontIncWithLines:
268 // fall through
269 case IncWithLines:
270 // fall through
271 case Include:
272 // fall through
273 case DontInclude:
274 parser()->readTextFileByName(m_file,m_text);
275 parser()->context.includeFileName = m_file;
276 parser()->context.includeFileText = m_text;
277 parser()->context.includeFileOffset = 0;
278 parser()->context.includeFileLength = m_text.length();
279 parser()->context.includeFileLine = 0;
280 parser()->context.includeFileShowLineNo = (m_type == DontIncWithLines || m_type == IncWithLines);
281 //printf("parser->context.includeFile=<<%s>>\n",qPrint(parser->context.includeFileText));
282 break;
283 case VerbInclude:
284 // fall through
285 case HtmlInclude:
286 case LatexInclude:
287 case DocInclude::RtfInclude:
288 case DocInclude::ManInclude:
289 case DocInclude::XmlInclude:
290 case DocInclude::DocbookInclude:
291 parser()->readTextFileByName(m_file,m_text);
292 break;
293 case Snippet:
294 case SnipWithLines:
295 parser()->readTextFileByName(m_file,m_text);
296 // check here for the existence of the blockId inside the file, so we
297 // only generate the warning once.
298 int count;
299 if (!m_blockId.isEmpty() && (count=m_text.contains(m_blockId.data()))!=2)
300 {
301 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,
302 parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),
303 "block marked with %s for \\snippet should appear twice in file %s, found it %d times\n",
304 qPrint(m_blockId),qPrint(m_file),count);
305 }
306 break;
307 case DocInclude::SnippetDoc:
308 case DocInclude::IncludeDoc:
309 err("Internal inconsistency: found switch SnippetDoc / IncludeDoc in file: %s"
310 "Please create a bug report\n",__FILE__);
311 break;
312 }
313}

315//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
316
317void DocIncOperator::parse(DocNodeVariant *)
318{
319 if (parser()->context.includeFileName.isEmpty())
320 {
321 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),
322 "No previous '\\include' or '\\dontinclude' command for '\\%s' present",
323 typeAsString());
324 }
325
326 m_includeFileName = parser()->context.includeFileName;
327 const char *p = parser()->context.includeFileText.data();
328 uint l = parser()->context.includeFileLength;
329 uint o = parser()->context.includeFileOffset;
330 int il = parser()->context.includeFileLine;
331 DBG(("DocIncOperator::parse() text=%s off=%d len=%d\n",p,o,l));
332 uint so = o,bo;
333 bool nonEmpty = FALSE;
334 switch(type())
335 {
336 case Line:
337 while (o<l)
338 {
339 char c = p[o];
340 if (c=='\n')
341 {
342 parser()->context.includeFileLine++;
343 if (nonEmpty) break; // we have a pattern to match
344 so=o+1; // no pattern, skip empty line
345 }
346 else if (!isspace(static_cast<uchar>(c))) // no white space char
347 {
348 nonEmpty=TRUE;
349 }
350 o++;
351 }
352 if (parser()->context.includeFileText.mid(so,o-so).find(m_pattern)!=-1)
353 {
354 m_line = il;
355 m_text = parser()->context.includeFileText.mid(so,o-so);
356 DBG(("DocIncOperator::parse() Line: %s\n",qPrint(m_text)));
357 }
358 parser()->context.includeFileOffset = std::min(l,o+1); // set pointer to start of new line
359 m_showLineNo = parser()->context.includeFileShowLineNo;
360 break;
361 case SkipLine:
362 while (o<l)
363 {
364 so=o;
365 while (o<l)
366 {
367 char c = p[o];
368 if (c=='\n')
369 {
370 parser()->context.includeFileLine++;
371 if (nonEmpty) break; // we have a pattern to match
372 so=o+1; // no pattern, skip empty line
373 }
374 else if (!isspace(static_cast<uchar>(c))) // no white space char
375 {
376 nonEmpty=TRUE;
377 }
378 o++;
379 }
380 if (parser()->context.includeFileText.mid(so,o-so).find(m_pattern)!=-1)
381 {
382 m_line = il;
383 m_text = parser()->context.includeFileText.mid(so,o-so);
384 DBG(("DocIncOperator::parse() SkipLine: %s\n",qPrint(m_text)));
385 break;
386 }
387 o++; // skip new line
388 }
389 parser()->context.includeFileOffset = std::min(l,o+1); // set pointer to start of new line
390 m_showLineNo = parser()->context.includeFileShowLineNo;
391 break;
392 case Skip:
393 while (o<l)
394 {
395 so=o;
396 while (o<l)
397 {
398 char c = p[o];
399 if (c=='\n')
400 {
401 parser()->context.includeFileLine++;
402 if (nonEmpty) break; // we have a pattern to match
403 so=o+1; // no pattern, skip empty line
404 }
405 else if (!isspace(static_cast<uchar>(c))) // no white space char
406 {
407 nonEmpty=TRUE;
408 }
409 o++;
410 }
411 if (parser()->context.includeFileText.mid(so,o-so).find(m_pattern)!=-1)
412 {
413 break;
414 }
415 o++; // skip new line
416 }
417 parser()->context.includeFileOffset = so; // set pointer to start of new line
418 m_showLineNo = parser()->context.includeFileShowLineNo;
419 break;
420 case Until:
421 bo=o;
422 while (o<l)
423 {
424 so=o;
425 while (o<l)
426 {
427 char c = p[o];
428 if (c=='\n')
429 {
430 parser()->context.includeFileLine++;
431 if (nonEmpty) break; // we have a pattern to match
432 so=o+1; // no pattern, skip empty line
433 }
434 else if (!isspace(static_cast<uchar>(c))) // no white space char
435 {
436 nonEmpty=TRUE;
437 }
438 o++;
439 }
440 if (parser()->context.includeFileText.mid(so,o-so).find(m_pattern)!=-1)
441 {
442 m_line = il;
443 m_text = parser()->context.includeFileText.mid(bo,o-bo);
444 DBG(("DocIncOperator::parse() Until: %s\n",qPrint(m_text)));
445 break;
446 }
447 o++; // skip new line
448 }
449 parser()->context.includeFileOffset = std::min(l,o+1); // set pointer to start of new line
450 m_showLineNo = parser()->context.includeFileShowLineNo;
451 break;
452 }
453}

457DocXRefItem::DocXRefItem(DocParser *parser,DocNodeVariant *parent,int id,const QCString &key) :
458 DocCompoundNode(parser,parent), m_id(id), m_key(key), m_relPath(parser->context.relPath)
459{
460}
461
462bool DocXRefItem::parse(DocNodeVariant *thisVariant)
463{
464 RefList *refList = RefListManager::instance().find(m_key);
465 if (refList && refList->isEnabled())
466 {
467 RefItem *item = refList->find(m_id);
468 ASSERT(item!=0);
469 if (item)
470 {
471 if (parser()->context.memberDef && parser()->context.memberDef->name().at(0)=='@')
472 {
473 m_file = "@"; // can't cross reference anonymous enum
474 m_anchor = "@";
475 }
476 else
477 {
478 m_file = refList->fileName();
479 m_anchor = item->anchor();
480 }
481 m_title = refList->sectionTitle();
482 //printf("DocXRefItem: file=%s anchor=%s title=%s\n",
483 // qPrint(m_file),qPrint(m_anchor),qPrint(m_title));
484
485 if (!item->text().isEmpty())
486 {
487 parser()->pushContext();
488 parser()->internalValidatingParseDoc(thisVariant,children(),item->text());
489 parser()->popContext();
490 }
491 }
492 return TRUE;
493 }
494 return FALSE;
495}

518DocSecRefItem::DocSecRefItem(DocParser *parser,DocNodeVariant *parent,const QCString &target) :
519 DocCompoundNode(parser,parent), m_target(target), m_relPath(parser->context.relPath)
520{
521}
522
523void DocSecRefItem::parse(DocNodeVariant *thisVariant)
524{
525 DBG(("DocSecRefItem::parse() start\n"));
526 auto ns = AutoNodeStack(parser(),thisVariant);
527
528 parser()->tokenizer.setStateTitle();
529 int tok;
530 while ((tok=parser()->tokenizer.lex()))
531 {
532 if (!parser()->defaultHandleToken(thisVariant,tok,children()))
533 {
534 parser()->errorHandleDefaultToken(thisVariant,tok,children(),"\\refitem");
535 }
536 }
537 parser()->tokenizer.setStatePara();
538 parser()->handlePendingStyleCommands(thisVariant,children());
539
540 if (!m_target.isEmpty())
541 {
542 SrcLangExt lang = getLanguageFromFileName(m_target);
543 const SectionInfo *sec = SectionManager::instance().find(m_target);
544 if (sec==0 && lang==SrcLangExt_Markdown) // lookup as markdown file
545 {
546 sec = SectionManager::instance().find(markdownFileNameToId(m_target));
547 }
548 if (sec) // ref to section or anchor
549 {
550 // set defaults
551 m_ref = sec->ref();
552 m_file = stripKnownExtensions(sec->fileName());
553 m_refType = Section;
554 m_anchor = sec->label();
555 m_isSubPage = false;
556 // adjust if needed
557 switch (sec->type())
558 {
559 case SectionType::Page:
560 {
561 PageDef *pd = Doxygen::pageLinkedMap->find(m_target);
562 m_isSubPage = pd && pd->hasParentPage();
563 if (!m_isSubPage)
564 {
565 m_anchor="";
566 }
567 }
568 break;
569 case SectionType::Anchor:
570 m_refType = Anchor;
571 break;
572 case SectionType::Table:
573 m_refType = Table;
574 break;
575 default:
576 break;
577 }
578 //printf("m_ref=%s,m_file=%s,type=%d\n",
579 // qPrint(m_ref),qPrint(m_file),m_refType);
580 }
581 else
582 {
583 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"reference to unknown section %s",
584 qPrint(m_target));
585 }
586 }
587 else
588 {
589 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"reference to empty target");
590 }
591
592 DBG(("DocSecRefItem::parse() end\n"));
593}

595//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
596
597void DocSecRefList::parse(DocNodeVariant *thisVariant)
598{
599 DBG(("DocSecRefList::parse() start\n"));
600 auto ns = AutoNodeStack(parser(),thisVariant);
601
602 int tok=parser()->tokenizer.lex();
603 // skip white space
604 while (tok==TK_WHITESPACE || tok==TK_NEWPARA) tok=parser()->tokenizer.lex();
605 // handle items
606 while (tok)
607 {
608 if (tok==TK_COMMAND_AT || tok == TK_COMMAND_BS)
609 {
610 const char *cmd_start = (tok==TK_COMMAND_AT ? "@" : "\\");
611 switch (Mappers::cmdMapper->map(parser()->context.token->name))
612 {
613 case CMD_SECREFITEM:
614 {
615 tok=parser()->tokenizer.lex();
616 if (tok!=TK_WHITESPACE)
617 {
618 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"expected whitespace after \\refitem command");
619 break;
620 }
621 tok=parser()->tokenizer.lex();
622 if (tok!=TK_WORD && tok!=TK_LNKWORD)
623 {
624 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"unexpected token %s as the argument of \\refitem",
625 DocTokenizer::tokToString(tok));
626 break;
627 }
628
629 auto vDocSecRefItem = children().append<DocSecRefItem>(parser(),thisVariant,parser()->context.token->name);
630 children().get_last<DocSecRefItem>()->parse(vDocSecRefItem);
631 }
632 break;
633 case CMD_ENDSECREFLIST:
634 goto endsecreflist;
635 default:
636 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"Illegal command %s as part of a \\secreflist",
637 qPrint(cmd_start + parser()->context.token->name));
638 goto endsecreflist;
639 }
640 }
641 else if (tok==TK_WHITESPACE)
642 {
643 // ignore whitespace
644 }
645 else
646 {
647 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"Unexpected token %s inside section reference list",
648 DocTokenizer::tokToString(tok));
649 goto endsecreflist;
650 }
651 tok=parser()->tokenizer.lex();
652 }
653
654endsecreflist:
655 DBG(("DocSecRefList::parse() end\n"));
656}

660DocInternalRef::DocInternalRef(DocParser *parser,DocNodeVariant *parent,const QCString &ref)
661 : DocCompoundNode(parser,parent), m_relPath(parser->context.relPath)
662{
663 int i=ref.find('#');
664 if (i!=-1)
665 {
666 m_anchor = ref.right(static_cast<int>(ref.length())-i-1);
667 m_file = ref.left(i);
668 }
669 else
670 {
671 m_file = ref;
672 }
673}
674
675void DocInternalRef::parse(DocNodeVariant *thisVariant)
676{
677 auto ns = AutoNodeStack(parser(),thisVariant);
678 DBG(("DocInternalRef::parse() start\n"));
679
680 int tok;
681 while ((tok=parser()->tokenizer.lex()))
682 {
683 if (!parser()->defaultHandleToken(thisVariant,tok,children()))
684 {
685 parser()->errorHandleDefaultToken(thisVariant,tok,children(),"\\ref");
686 }
687 }
688
689 parser()->handlePendingStyleCommands(thisVariant,children());
690 DBG(("DocInternalRef::parse() end\n"));
691}

693//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
694
695DocRef::DocRef(DocParser *parser,DocNodeVariant *parent,const QCString &target,const QCString &context) :
696 DocCompoundNode(parser,parent), m_refType(Unknown), m_isSubPage(FALSE)
697{
698 const Definition *compound = 0;
699 QCString anchor;
700 //printf("DocRef::DocRef(target=%s,context=%s)\n",qPrint(target),qPrint(context));
701 ASSERT(!target.isEmpty());
702 SrcLangExt lang = getLanguageFromFileName(target);
703 m_relPath = parser->context.relPath;
704 const SectionInfo *sec = SectionManager::instance().find(target);
705 if (sec==0 && lang==SrcLangExt_Markdown) // lookup as markdown file
706 {
707 sec = SectionManager::instance().find(markdownFileNameToId(target));
708 }
709 if (sec) // ref to section or anchor
710 {
711 PageDef *pd = 0;
712 if (sec->type()==SectionType::Page)
713 {
714 pd = Doxygen::pageLinkedMap->find(target);
715 }
716 m_text = sec->title();
717 if (m_text.isEmpty()) m_text = sec->label();
718
719 m_ref = sec->ref();
720 m_file = stripKnownExtensions(sec->fileName());
721 if (sec->type()==SectionType::Anchor)
722 {
723 m_refType = Anchor;
724 }
725 else if (sec->type()==SectionType::Table)
726 {
727 m_refType = Table;
728 }
729 else
730 {
731 m_refType = Section;
732 }
733 m_isSubPage = pd && pd->hasParentPage();
734 if (sec->type()!=SectionType::Page || m_isSubPage) m_anchor = sec->label();
735 m_sectionType = sec->type();
736 //printf("m_text=%s,m_ref=%s,m_file=%s,type=%d\n",
737 // qPrint(m_text),qPrint(m_ref),qPrint(m_file),m_refType);
738 return;
739 }
740 else if (resolveLink(context,target,TRUE,&compound,anchor))
741 {
742 bool isFile = compound ?
743 (compound->definitionType()==Definition::TypeFile ||
744 compound->definitionType()==Definition::TypePage ? TRUE : FALSE) :
745 FALSE;
746 m_text = linkToText(compound?compound->getLanguage():SrcLangExt_Unknown,target,isFile);
747 m_anchor = anchor;
748 if (compound && compound->isLinkable()) // ref to compound
749 {
750 if (anchor.isEmpty() && /* compound link */
751 compound->definitionType()==Definition::TypeGroup && /* is group */
752 !toGroupDef(compound)->groupTitle().isEmpty() /* with title */
753 )
754 {
755 m_text=(toGroupDef(compound))->groupTitle(); // use group's title as link
756 }
757 else if (compound->definitionType()==Definition::TypeMember &&
758 toMemberDef(compound)->isObjCMethod())
759 {
760 // Objective C Method
761 const MemberDef *member = toMemberDef(compound);
762 bool localLink = parser->context.memberDef ? member->getClassDef()==parser->context.memberDef->getClassDef() : FALSE;
763 m_text = member->objCMethodName(localLink,parser->context.inSeeBlock);
764 }
765
766 m_file = compound->getOutputFileBase();
767 m_ref = compound->getReference();
768 //printf("isFile=%d compound=%s (%d)\n",isFile,qPrint(compound->name()),
769 // compound->definitionType());
770 return;
771 }
772 else if (compound && compound->definitionType()==Definition::TypeFile &&
773 toFileDef(compound)->generateSourceFile()
774 ) // undocumented file that has source code we can link to
775 {
776 m_file = compound->getSourceFileBase();
777 m_ref = compound->getReference();
778 return;
779 }
780 }
781 m_text = target;
782 warn_doc_error(parser->context.fileName,parser->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"unable to resolve reference to '%s' for \\ref command",
783 qPrint(target));
784}
785
786static void flattenParagraphs(DocNodeVariant *root,DocNodeList &children)
787{
788 DocNodeList newChildren;
789 for (auto &dn : children)
790 {
791 DocPara *para = std::get_if<DocPara>(&dn);
792 if (para)
793 {
794 //// move the children of the paragraph to the end of the newChildren list
795 newChildren.move_append(para->children());
796 }
797 }
798
799 // replace the children list by the newChildren list
800 children.clear();
801 children.move_append(newChildren);
802 // reparent the children
803 for (auto &cn : children)
804 {
805 setParent(&cn,root);
806 }
807}

809void DocRef::parse(DocNodeVariant *thisVariant)
810{
811 auto ns = AutoNodeStack(parser(),thisVariant);
812 DBG(("DocRef::parse() start\n"));
813
814 int tok;
815 while ((tok=parser()->tokenizer.lex()))
816 {
817 if (!parser()->defaultHandleToken(thisVariant,tok,children()))
818 {
819 switch (tok)
820 {
821 case TK_HTMLTAG:
822 break;
823 default:
824 parser()->errorHandleDefaultToken(thisVariant,tok,children(),"\\ref");
825 break;
826 }
827 }
828 }
829
830 if (children().empty() && !m_text.isEmpty())
831 {
832 parser()->context.insideHtmlLink=TRUE;
833 parser()->pushContext();
834 parser()->internalValidatingParseDoc(thisVariant,children(),m_text);
835 parser()->popContext();
836 parser()->context.insideHtmlLink=FALSE;
837 flattenParagraphs(thisVariant,children());
838 }
839
840 parser()->handlePendingStyleCommands(thisVariant,children());
841}

884{

887 m_refText = target;
888 m_relPath = parser->context.relPath;

890 {

905 m_file = compound->getSourceFileBase();
906 m_ref = compound->getReference();
907 }
908 return;
909 }
910
911 // bogus link target
912 warn_doc_error(parser->context.fileName,parser->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"unable to resolve link to '%s' for \\link command",
913 qPrint(target));
914}
915
916
917QCString DocLink::parse(DocNodeVariant *thisVariant,bool isJavaLink,bool isXmlLink)
918{
919 QCString result;
920 auto ns = AutoNodeStack(parser(),thisVariant);
921 DBG(("DocLink::parse() start\n"));
922
923 int tok;
924 while ((tok=parser()->tokenizer.lex()))
925 {
926 if (!parser()->defaultHandleToken(thisVariant,tok,children(),FALSE))
927 {
928 const char *cmd_start = "\\";
929 switch (tok)
930 {
931 case TK_COMMAND_AT:
932 cmd_start = "@";
933 // fall through
934 case TK_COMMAND_BS:
935 switch (Mappers::cmdMapper->map(parser()->context.token->name))
936 {
937 case CMD_ENDLINK:
938 if (isJavaLink)
939 {
940 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"{@link.. ended with @endlink command");
941 }
942 goto endlink;
943 default:
944 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"Illegal command %s as part of a \\link",
945 qPrint(cmd_start + parser()->context.token->name));
946 break;
947 }
948 break;
949 case TK_SYMBOL:
950 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"Unsupported symbol %s found as part of a \\link",
951 qPrint(parser()->context.token->name));
952 break;
953 case TK_HTMLTAG:
954 if (parser()->context.token->name!="see" || !isXmlLink)
955 {
956 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"Unexpected xml/html command %s found as part of a \\link",
957 qPrint(parser()->context.token->name));
958 }
959 goto endlink;
960 case TK_LNKWORD:
961 case TK_WORD:
962 if (isJavaLink) // special case to detect closing }
963 {
964 QCString w = parser()->context.token->name;
965 int p;
966 if (w=="}")
967 {
968 goto endlink;
969 }
970 else if ((p=w.find('}'))!=-1)
971 {
972 uint l=w.length();
973 children().append<DocWord>(parser(),thisVariant,w.left(p));
974 if (static_cast<uint>(p)<l-1) // something left after the } (for instance a .)
975 {
976 result=w.right(static_cast<int>(l)-p-1);
977 }
978 goto endlink;
979 }
980 }
981 children().append<DocWord>(parser(),thisVariant,parser()->context.token->name);
982 break;
983 default:
984 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"Unexpected token %s",
985 DocTokenizer::tokToString(tok));
986 break;
987 }
988 }
989 }
990 if (tok==0)
991 {
992 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,
993 parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),
994 "Unexpected end of comment while inside link command\n");
995 }
996endlink:
997
998 if (children().empty()) // no link text
999 {
1000 children().append<DocWord>(parser(),thisVariant,m_refText);
1001 }
1002
1003 parser()->handlePendingStyleCommands(thisVariant,children());
1004 DBG(("DocLink::parse() end\n"));
1005 return result;
1006}

1180//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
1181
1182int DocHtmlHeader::parse(DocNodeVariant *thisVariant)
1183{
1184 int retval=RetVal_OK;
1185 auto ns = AutoNodeStack(parser(),thisVariant);
1186 DBG(("DocHtmlHeader::parse() start\n"));
1187
1188 int tok;
1189 while ((tok=parser()->tokenizer.lex()))
1190 {
1191 if (!parser()->defaultHandleToken(thisVariant,tok,children()))
1192 {
1193 switch (tok)
1194 {
1195 case TK_HTMLTAG:
1196 {
1197 int tagId=Mappers::htmlTagMapper->map(parser()->context.token->name);
1198 if (tagId==HTML_H1 && parser()->context.token->endTag) // found </h1> tag
1199 {
1200 if (m_level!=1)
1201 {
1202 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"<h%d> ended with </h1>",
1203 m_level);
1204 }
1205 goto endheader;
1206 }
1207 else if (tagId==HTML_H2 && parser()->context.token->endTag) // found </h2> tag
1208 {
1209 if (m_level!=2)
1210 {
1211 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"<h%d> ended with </h2>",
1212 m_level);
1213 }
1214 goto endheader;
1215 }
1216 else if (tagId==HTML_H3 && parser()->context.token->endTag) // found </h3> tag
1217 {
1218 if (m_level!=3)
1219 {
1220 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"<h%d> ended with </h3>",
1221 m_level);
1222 }
1223 goto endheader;
1224 }
1225 else if (tagId==HTML_H4 && parser()->context.token->endTag) // found </h4> tag
1226 {
1227 if (m_level!=4)
1228 {
1229 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"<h%d> ended with </h4>",
1230 m_level);
1231 }
1232 goto endheader;
1233 }
1234 else if (tagId==HTML_H5 && parser()->context.token->endTag) // found </h5> tag
1235 {
1236 if (m_level!=5)
1237 {
1238 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"<h%d> ended with </h5>",
1239 m_level);
1240 }
1241 goto endheader;
1242 }
1243 else if (tagId==HTML_H6 && parser()->context.token->endTag) // found </h6> tag
1244 {
1245 if (m_level!=6)
1246 {
1247 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"<h%d> ended with </h6>",
1248 m_level);
1249 }
1250 goto endheader;
1251 }
1252 else if (tagId==HTML_A)
1253 {
1254 if (!parser()->context.token->endTag)
1255 {
1256 parser()->handleAHref(thisVariant,children(),parser()->context.token->attribs);
1257 }
1258 }
1259 else if (tagId==HTML_BR)
1260 {
1261 children().append<DocLineBreak>(parser(),thisVariant,parser()->context.token->attribs);
1262 }
1263 else
1264 {
1265 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"Unexpected html tag <%s%s> found within <h%d> context",
1266 parser()->context.token->endTag?"/":"",qPrint(parser()->context.token->name),m_level);
1267 }
1268 }
1269 break;
1270 default:
1271 char tmp[20];
1272 sprintf(tmp,"<h%d>tag",m_level);
1273 parser()->errorHandleDefaultToken(thisVariant,tok,children(),tmp);
1274 }
1275 }
1276 }
1277 if (tok==0)
1278 {
1279 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"Unexpected end of comment while inside"
1280 " <h%d> tag\n",m_level);
1281 }
1282endheader:
1283 parser()->handlePendingStyleCommands(thisVariant,children());
1284 DBG(("DocHtmlHeader::parse() end\n"));
1285 return retval;
1286}

1289void DocHtmlSummary::parse(DocNodeVariant *thisVariant)
1290{
1291 DBG(("DocHtmlSummary::parse() start\n"));
1292 auto ns = AutoNodeStack(parser(),thisVariant);
1293 parser()->tokenizer.setStateTitle();
1294 int tok;
1295 while ((tok=parser()->tokenizer.lex()))
1296 {
1297 int tagId;
1298 // check of </summary>
1299 if (tok==TK_HTMLTAG &&
1300 (tagId=Mappers::htmlTagMapper->map(parser()->context.token->name)) && tagId==XML_SUMMARY &&
1301 parser()->context.token->endTag
1302 )
1303 {
1304 break;
1305 }
1306 else if (!parser()->defaultHandleToken(thisVariant,tok,children()))

1308 parser()->errorHandleDefaultToken(thisVariant,tok,children(),"summary section");
1309 }
1310 }
1311 parser()->tokenizer.setStatePara();
1312}

1314//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
1315
1316int DocHtmlDetails::parse(DocNodeVariant *thisVariant)
1317{
1318 DBG(("DocHtmlDetails::parse() start\n"));
1319 int retval=0;
1320 auto ns = AutoNodeStack(parser(),thisVariant);
1321
1322 // parse one or more paragraphs
1323 bool isFirst=TRUE;
1324 DocPara *par=0;
1325 do
1326 {
1327 auto vDocPara = children().append<DocPara>(parser(),thisVariant);
1328 par = children().get_last<DocPara>();
1329 if (isFirst) { par->markFirst(); isFirst=FALSE; }
1330 retval=par->parse(vDocPara);
1331 }
1332 while (retval==TK_NEWPARA);
1333 if (par) par->markLast();
1334
1335 if (!summary())
1336 {
1337 HtmlAttribList summaryAttribs;
1338 m_summary = std::make_unique<DocNodeVariant>(DocHtmlSummary(parser(),thisVariant,summaryAttribs));
1339 DocHtmlSummary *summary = &std::get<DocHtmlSummary>(*m_summary);
1340 summary->children().append<DocWord>(parser(),thisVariant,theTranslator->trDetails());
1341 }
1342 DBG(("DocHtmlDetails::parse() end retval=%s\n",DocTokenizer::retvalToString(retval)));
1343 return (retval==RetVal_EndHtmlDetails) ? RetVal_OK : retval;
1344}

1349 m_summary = std::make_unique<DocNodeVariant>(DocHtmlSummary(parser(),thisVariant,attribs));
1350 DocHtmlSummary *summary = &std::get<DocHtmlSummary>(*m_summary);
1351 summary->parse(m_summary.get());
1352 DBG(("DocHtmlDetails::parseSummary() end\n"));
1353}

1357int DocHRef::parse(DocNodeVariant *thisVariant)
1358{
1359 int retval=RetVal_OK;
1360 auto ns = AutoNodeStack(parser(),thisVariant);
1361 DBG(("DocHRef::parse() start\n"));
1362
1363 int tok;
1364 while ((tok=parser()->tokenizer.lex()))
1365 {
1366 if (!parser()->defaultHandleToken(thisVariant,tok,children()))
1367 {
1368 switch (tok)
1369 {
1370 case TK_HTMLTAG:
1371 {
1372 int tagId=Mappers::htmlTagMapper->map(parser()->context.token->name);
1373 if (tagId==HTML_A && parser()->context.token->endTag) // found </a> tag
1374 {
1375 goto endhref;
1376 }
1377 else if (tagId==HTML_BR)
1378 {
1379 children().append<DocLineBreak>(parser(),thisVariant,parser()->context.token->attribs);
1380 }
1381 else
1382 {
1383 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"Unexpected html tag <%s%s> found within <a href=...> context",
1384 parser()->context.token->endTag?"/":"",qPrint(parser()->context.token->name));
1385 }
1386 }
1387 break;
1388 default:
1389 parser()->errorHandleDefaultToken(thisVariant,tok,children(),"<a>..</a> block");
1390 break;
1391 }
1392 }
1393 }
1394 if (tok==0)
1395 {
1396 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"Unexpected end of comment while inside"
1397 " <a href=...> tag");
1398 }
1399endhref:
1400 parser()->handlePendingStyleCommands(thisVariant,children());
1401 DBG(("DocHRef::parse() end\n"));
1402 return retval;
1403}

1405//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
1406
1407int DocInternal::parse(DocNodeVariant *thisVariant,int level)
1408{
1409 int retval=RetVal_OK;
1410 auto ns = AutoNodeStack(parser(),thisVariant);
1411 DBG(("DocInternal::parse() start\n"));
1412
1413 // first parse any number of paragraphs
1414 bool isFirst=TRUE;
1415 DocPara *lastPar=0;
1416 do
1417 {
1418 auto vDocPara = children().append<DocPara>(parser(),thisVariant);
1419 DocPara *par = children().get_last<DocPara>();
1420 if (isFirst) { par->markFirst(); isFirst=FALSE; }
1421 retval=par->parse(vDocPara);
1422 if (!par->isEmpty())
1423 {
1424 if (lastPar) lastPar->markLast(FALSE);
1425 lastPar=par;
1426 }
1427 else
1428 {
1429 children().pop_back();
1430 }
1431 if (retval==TK_LISTITEM)
1432 {
1433 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"Invalid list item found");
1434 }
1435 } while (retval!=0 &&
1436 retval!=RetVal_Section &&
1437 retval!=RetVal_Subsection &&
1438 retval!=RetVal_Subsubsection &&
1439 retval!=RetVal_Paragraph &&
1440 retval!=RetVal_EndInternal
1441 );
1442 if (lastPar) lastPar->markLast();
1443
1444 // then parse any number of level-n sections
1445 while ((level==1 && retval==RetVal_Section) ||
1446 (level==2 && retval==RetVal_Subsection) ||
1447 (level==3 && retval==RetVal_Subsubsection) ||
1448 (level==4 && retval==RetVal_Paragraph)
1449 )
1450 {
1451 auto vDocSection = children().append<DocSection>(parser(),thisVariant,
1452 std::min(level+Doxygen::subpageNestingLevel,5),
1453 parser()->context.token->sectionId);
1454 retval = children().get_last<DocSection>()->parse(vDocSection);
1455 }
1456
1457 if (retval==RetVal_Internal)
1458 {
1459 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"\\internal command found inside internal section");
1460 }
1461
1462 DBG(("DocInternal::parse() end: retval=%s\n",DocTokenizer::retvalToString(retval)));
1463 return retval;
1464}

1466//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
1467
1468int DocIndexEntry::parse(DocNodeVariant *thisVariant)
1469{
1470 int retval=RetVal_OK;
1471 auto ns = AutoNodeStack(parser(),thisVariant);
1472 DBG(("DocIndexEntry::parse() start\n"));
1473 int tok=parser()->tokenizer.lex();
1474 if (tok!=TK_WHITESPACE)
1475 {
1476 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"expected whitespace after \\addindex command");
1477 goto endindexentry;
1478 }
1479 parser()->tokenizer.setStateTitle();
1480 m_entry="";
1481 while ((tok=parser()->tokenizer.lex()))
1482 {
1483 switch (tok)
1484 {
1485 case TK_WHITESPACE:
1486 m_entry+=" ";
1487 break;
1488 case TK_WORD:
1489 case TK_LNKWORD:
1490 m_entry+=parser()->context.token->name;
1491 break;
1492 case TK_SYMBOL:
1493 {
1494 HtmlEntityMapper::SymType s = DocSymbol::decodeSymbol(parser()->context.token->name);
1495 switch (s)
1496 {
1497 case HtmlEntityMapper::Sym_BSlash: m_entry+='\\'; break;
1498 case HtmlEntityMapper::Sym_At: m_entry+='@'; break;
1499 case HtmlEntityMapper::Sym_Less: m_entry+='<'; break;
1500 case HtmlEntityMapper::Sym_Greater: m_entry+='>'; break;
1501 case HtmlEntityMapper::Sym_Amp: m_entry+='&'; break;
1502 case HtmlEntityMapper::Sym_Dollar: m_entry+='$'; break;
1503 case HtmlEntityMapper::Sym_Hash: m_entry+='#'; break;
1504 case HtmlEntityMapper::Sym_Percent: m_entry+='%'; break;
1505 case HtmlEntityMapper::Sym_apos: m_entry+='\''; break;
1506 case HtmlEntityMapper::Sym_Quot: m_entry+='"'; break;
1507 case HtmlEntityMapper::Sym_lsquo: m_entry+='`'; break;
1508 case HtmlEntityMapper::Sym_rsquo: m_entry+='\''; break;
1509 case HtmlEntityMapper::Sym_ldquo: m_entry+="``"; break;
1510 case HtmlEntityMapper::Sym_rdquo: m_entry+="''"; break;
1511 case HtmlEntityMapper::Sym_ndash: m_entry+="--"; break;
1512 case HtmlEntityMapper::Sym_mdash: m_entry+="---"; break;
1513 default:
1514 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"Unexpected symbol found as argument of \\addindex");
1515 break;
1516 }
1517 }
1518 break;
1519 case TK_COMMAND_AT:
1520 // fall through
1521 case TK_COMMAND_BS:
1522 switch (Mappers::cmdMapper->map(parser()->context.token->name))
1523 {
1524 case CMD_BSLASH: m_entry+='\\'; break;
1525 case CMD_AT: m_entry+='@'; break;
1526 case CMD_LESS: m_entry+='<'; break;
1527 case CMD_GREATER: m_entry+='>'; break;
1528 case CMD_AMP: m_entry+='&'; break;
1529 case CMD_DOLLAR: m_entry+='$'; break;
1530 case CMD_HASH: m_entry+='#'; break;
1531 case CMD_DCOLON: m_entry+="::"; break;
1532 case CMD_PERCENT: m_entry+='%'; break;
1533 case CMD_NDASH: m_entry+="--"; break;
1534 case CMD_MDASH: m_entry+="---"; break;
1535 case CMD_QUOTE: m_entry+='"'; break;
1536 case CMD_PUNT: m_entry+='.'; break;
1537 case CMD_PLUS: m_entry+='+'; break;
1538 case CMD_MINUS: m_entry+='-'; break;
1539 case CMD_EQUAL: m_entry+='='; break;
1540 default:
1541 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"Unexpected command %s found as argument of \\addindex",
1542 qPrint(parser()->context.token->name));
1543 break;
1544 }
1545 break;
1546 default:
1547 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"Unexpected token %s",
1548 DocTokenizer::tokToString(tok));
1549 break;
1550 }
1551 }
1552 parser()->tokenizer.setStatePara();
1553 m_entry = m_entry.stripWhiteSpace();
1554endindexentry:
1555 DBG(("DocIndexEntry::parse() end retval=%s\n",DocTokenizer::retvalToString(retval)));
1556 return retval;
1557}

1589int DocHtmlCaption::parse(DocNodeVariant *thisVariant)
1590{
1591 int retval=0;
1592 auto ns = AutoNodeStack(parser(),thisVariant);
1593 DBG(("DocHtmlCaption::parse() start\n"));
1594 int tok;
1595 while ((tok=parser()->tokenizer.lex()))
1596 {
1597 if (!parser()->defaultHandleToken(thisVariant,tok,children()))
1598 {
1599 switch (tok)
1600 {
1601 case TK_HTMLTAG:
1602 {
1603 int tagId=Mappers::htmlTagMapper->map(parser()->context.token->name);
1604 if (tagId==HTML_CAPTION && parser()->context.token->endTag) // found </caption> tag
1605 {
1606 retval = RetVal_OK;
1607 goto endcaption;
1608 }
1609 else
1610 {
1611 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"Unexpected html tag <%s%s> found within <caption> context",
1612 parser()->context.token->endTag?"/":"",qPrint(parser()->context.token->name));
1613 }
1614 }
1615 break;
1616 default:
1617 parser()->errorHandleDefaultToken(thisVariant,tok,children(),"<caption> tag");
1618 break;
1619 }
1620 }
1621 }
1622 if (tok==0)
1623 {
1624 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"Unexpected end of comment while inside"
1625 " <caption> tag");
1626 }
1627endcaption:
1628 parser()->handlePendingStyleCommands(thisVariant,children());
1629 DBG(("DocHtmlCaption::parse() end\n"));
1630 return retval;
1631}

1728
1729DocHtmlCell::Alignment DocHtmlCell::alignment() const
1730{
1731 for (const auto &attr : attribs())
1732 {
1733 QCString attrName = attr.name.lower();
1734 QCString attrValue = attr.value.lower();
1735 if (attrName=="align")
1736 {
1737 if (attrValue=="center")
1738 return Center;
1739 else if (attrValue=="right")
1740 return Right;
1741 else return Left;
1742 }
1743 else if (attrName=="class" && attrValue.startsWith("markdowntable"))
1744 {
1745 if (attrValue=="markdowntableheadcenter")
1746 return Center;
1747 else if (attrValue=="markdowntableheadright")
1748 return Right;
1749 else if (attrValue=="markdowntableheadleft")
1750 return Left;
1751 else if (attrValue=="markdowntableheadnone")
1752 return Center;
1753 else if (attrValue=="markdowntablebodycenter")
1754 return Center;
1755 else if (attrValue=="markdowntablebodyright")
1756 return Right;
1757 else if (attrValue=="markdowntablebodyleft")
1758 return Left;
1759 else if (attrValue=="markdowntablebodynone")
1760 return Left;
1761 else return Left;
1762 }
1763 }
1764 return Left;
1765}
1766
1767DocHtmlCell::Valignment DocHtmlCell::valignment() const
1768{
1769 for (const auto &attr : attribs())
1770 {
1771 QCString attrName = attr.name.lower();
1772 QCString attrValue = attr.value.lower();
1773 if (attrName=="valign")
1774 {
1775 if (attrValue=="top")
1776 return Top;
1777 else if (attrValue=="bottom")
1778 return Bottom;
1779 else if (attrValue=="middle")
1780 return Middle;
1781 else return Middle;
1782 }
1783 }
1784 return Middle;
1785}

1789bool DocHtmlRow::isHeading() const
1790{ // a row is a table heading if all cells are marked as such
1791 bool heading=TRUE;
1792 for (const auto &n : children())
1793 {
1794 const DocHtmlCell *cell = std::get_if<DocHtmlCell>(&n);
1795 if (cell && !cell->isHeading())
1796 {
1797 heading = FALSE;
1798 break;
1799 }
1800 }
1801 return !children().empty() && heading;

1803
1804int DocHtmlRow::parse(DocNodeVariant *thisVariant)
1805{
1806 int retval=RetVal_OK;
1807 auto ns = AutoNodeStack(parser(),thisVariant);
1808 DBG(("DocHtmlRow::parse() start\n"));
1809
1810 bool isHeading=FALSE;
1811 bool isFirst=TRUE;
1812 DocHtmlCell *cell=0;
1813
1814 // get next token
1815 int tok=parser()->tokenizer.lex();
1816 // skip whitespace
1817 while (tok==TK_WHITESPACE || tok==TK_NEWPARA) tok=parser()->tokenizer.lex();
1818 // should find a html tag now
1819 if (tok==TK_HTMLTAG)
1820 {
1821 int tagId=Mappers::htmlTagMapper->map(parser()->context.token->name);
1822 if (tagId==HTML_TD && !parser()->context.token->endTag) // found <td> tag
1823 {
1824 }
1825 else if (tagId==HTML_TH && !parser()->context.token->endTag) // found <th> tag
1826 {
1827 isHeading=TRUE;
1828 }
1829 else // found some other tag
1830 {
1831 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"expected <td> or <th> tag but "
1832 "found <%s> instead!",qPrint(parser()->context.token->name));
1833 parser()->tokenizer.pushBackHtmlTag(parser()->context.token->name);
1834 goto endrow;
1835 }
1836 }
1837 else if (tok==0) // premature end of comment
1838 {
1839 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"unexpected end of comment while looking"
1840 " for a html description title");
1841 goto endrow;
1842 }
1843 else // token other than html token
1844 {
1845 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"expected <td> or <th> tag but found %s token instead!",
1846 DocTokenizer::tokToString(tok));
1847 goto endrow;
1848 }
1849
1850 // parse one or more cells
1851 do
1852 {
1853 auto vDocHtmlCell = children().append<DocHtmlCell>(parser(),thisVariant,
1854 parser()->context.token->attribs,
1855 isHeading);
1856 cell = children().get_last<DocHtmlCell>();
1857 cell->markFirst(isFirst);
1858 isFirst=FALSE;
1859 retval=cell->parse(vDocHtmlCell);
1860 isHeading = retval==RetVal_TableHCell;
1861 }
1862 while (retval==RetVal_TableCell || retval==RetVal_TableHCell);
1863 cell->markLast(TRUE);
1864
1865endrow:
1866 DBG(("DocHtmlRow::parse() end\n"));
1867 return retval;
1868}

1871{
1872 int retval=RetVal_OK;
1873 auto ns = AutoNodeStack(parser(),thisVariant);
1874 DBG(("DocHtmlRow::parseXml() start\n"));
1875
1876 bool isFirst=TRUE;
1877 DocHtmlCell *cell=0;
1878
1879 // get next token
1880 int tok=parser()->tokenizer.lex();
1881 // skip whitespace
1882 while (tok==TK_WHITESPACE || tok==TK_NEWPARA) tok=parser()->tokenizer.lex();
1883 // should find a html tag now
1884 if (tok==TK_HTMLTAG)
1885 {
1886 int tagId=Mappers::htmlTagMapper->map(parser()->context.token->name);
1887 if (tagId==XML_TERM && !parser()->context.token->endTag) // found <term> tag
1888 {
1889 }
1890 else if (tagId==XML_DESCRIPTION && !parser()->context.token->endTag) // found <description> tag
1891 {
1892 }
1893 else // found some other tag
1894 {
1895 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"expected <term> or <description> tag but "

1897 parser()->tokenizer.pushBackHtmlTag(parser()->context.token->name);
1898 goto endrow;
1899 }
1900 }
1901 else if (tok==0) // premature end of comment
1902 {
1903 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"unexpected end of comment while looking"

1905 goto endrow;
1906 }

1950
1951int DocHtmlTable::parse(DocNodeVariant *thisVariant)
1952{
1953 int retval=RetVal_OK;
1954 auto ns = AutoNodeStack(parser(),thisVariant);
1955 DBG(("DocHtmlTable::parse() start\n"));
1956
1957getrow:
1958 // get next token
1959 int tok=parser()->tokenizer.lex();
1960 // skip whitespace
1961 while (tok==TK_WHITESPACE || tok==TK_NEWPARA) tok=parser()->tokenizer.lex();
1962 // should find a html tag now
1963 if (tok==TK_HTMLTAG)
1964 {
1965 int tagId=Mappers::htmlTagMapper->map(parser()->context.token->name);
1966 if (tagId==HTML_TR && !parser()->context.token->endTag) // found <tr> tag
1967 {
1968 // no caption, just rows
1969 retval=RetVal_TableRow;
1970 }
1971 else if (tagId==HTML_CAPTION && !parser()->context.token->endTag) // found <caption> tag
1972 {
1973 if (m_caption)
1974 {
1975 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"table already has a caption, found another one");
1976 }
1977 else
1978 {
1979 m_caption = std::make_unique<DocNodeVariant>(
1980 DocHtmlCaption(parser(),thisVariant,parser()->context.token->attribs));
1981 retval=std::get<DocHtmlCaption>(*m_caption).parse(m_caption.get());
1982
1983 if (retval==RetVal_OK) // caption was parsed ok
1984 {
1985 goto getrow;
1986 }
1987 }
1988 }
1989 else // found wrong token
1990 {
1991 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"expected <tr> or <caption> tag but "
1992 "found <%s%s> instead!", parser()->context.token->endTag ? "/" : "", qPrint(parser()->context.token->name));
1993 }
1994 }
1995 else if (tok==0) // premature end of comment
1996 {
1997 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"unexpected end of comment while looking"
1998 " for a <tr> or <caption> tag");
1999 }
2000 else // token other than html token
2001 {
2002 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"expected <tr> tag but found %s token instead!",
2003 DocTokenizer::tokToString(tok));
2004 }
2005
2006 // parse one or more rows
2007 while (retval==RetVal_TableRow)
2008 {
2009 auto vDocHtmlRow = children().append<DocHtmlRow>(parser(),thisVariant,parser()->context.token->attribs);
2010 retval = children().get_last<DocHtmlRow>()->parse(vDocHtmlRow);
2011 }
2012
2013 computeTableGrid();
2014
2015 DBG(("DocHtmlTable::parse() end\n"));
2016 return retval==RetVal_EndTable ? RetVal_OK : retval;
2017}

2019int DocHtmlTable::parseXml(DocNodeVariant *thisVariant)
2020{
2021 int retval=RetVal_OK;
2022 auto ns = AutoNodeStack(parser(),thisVariant);
2023 DBG(("DocHtmlTable::parseXml() start\n"));
2024
2025 // get next token
2026 int tok=parser()->tokenizer.lex();
2027 // skip whitespace
2028 while (tok==TK_WHITESPACE || tok==TK_NEWPARA) tok=parser()->tokenizer.lex();
2029 // should find a html tag now
2030 int tagId=0;
2031 bool isHeader=FALSE;
2032 if (tok==TK_HTMLTAG)
2033 {
2034 tagId=Mappers::htmlTagMapper->map(parser()->context.token->name);
2035 if (tagId==XML_ITEM && !parser()->context.token->endTag) // found <item> tag
2036 {
2037 retval=RetVal_TableRow;
2038 }
2039 if (tagId==XML_LISTHEADER && !parser()->context.token->endTag) // found <listheader> tag
2040 {
2041 retval=RetVal_TableRow;
2042 isHeader=TRUE;
2043 }
2044 }
2045
2046 // parse one or more rows
2047 while (retval==RetVal_TableRow)
2048 {
2049 auto vDocHtmlRow = children().append<DocHtmlRow>(parser(),thisVariant,parser()->context.token->attribs);
2050 DocHtmlRow *tr = children().get_last<DocHtmlRow>();
2051 retval=tr->parseXml(vDocHtmlRow,isHeader);
2052 isHeader=FALSE;
2053 }
2054
2055 computeTableGrid();
2056
2057 DBG(("DocHtmlTable::parseXml() end\n"));
2058 tagId=Mappers::htmlTagMapper->map(parser()->context.token->name);
2059 return tagId==XML_LIST && parser()->context.token->endTag ? RetVal_OK : retval;
2060}
2061
2062/** Helper class to compute the grid for an HTML style table */
2063struct ActiveRowSpan
2064{
2065 ActiveRowSpan(uint rows,uint col) : rowsLeft(rows), column(col) {}
2066 uint rowsLeft;
2067 uint column;
2068};
2069
2070/** List of ActiveRowSpan classes. */
2071typedef std::vector<ActiveRowSpan> RowSpanList;
2072
2073/** determines the location of all cells in a grid, resolving row and
2074 column spans. For each the total number of visible cells is computed,
2075 and the total number of visible columns over all rows is stored.
2076 */
2077void DocHtmlTable::computeTableGrid()
2078{
2079 //printf("computeTableGrid()\n");
2080 RowSpanList rowSpans;
2081 uint maxCols=0;
2082 uint rowIdx=1;
2083 for (auto &rowNode : children())
2084 {
2085 uint colIdx=1;
2086 uint cells=0;
2087 DocHtmlRow *row = std::get_if<DocHtmlRow>(&rowNode);
2088 if (row)
2089 {
2090 size_t i;
2091 for (auto &cellNode : row->children())
2092 {
2093 DocHtmlCell *cell = std::get_if<DocHtmlCell>(&cellNode);
2094 if (cell)
2095 {
2096 uint rs = cell->rowSpan();
2097 uint cs = cell->colSpan();
2098
2099 for (i=0;i<rowSpans.size();i++)
2100 {
2101 if (rowSpans[i].rowsLeft>0 &&
2102 rowSpans[i].column==colIdx)
2103 {
2104 colIdx=rowSpans[i].column+1;
2105 cells++;
2106 }
2107 }
2108 if (rs>0) rowSpans.emplace_back(rs,colIdx);
2109 //printf("found cell at (%d,%d)\n",rowIdx,colIdx);
2110 cell->setRowIndex(rowIdx);
2111 cell->setColumnIndex(colIdx);
2112 colIdx+=cs;
2113 cells++;
2114 }
2115 }
2116 for (i=0;i<rowSpans.size();i++)
2117 {
2118 if (rowSpans[i].rowsLeft>0) rowSpans[i].rowsLeft--;
2119 }
2120 row->setVisibleCells(cells);
2121 row->setRowIndex(rowIdx);
2122 rowIdx++;
2123 }
2124 if (colIdx-1>maxCols) maxCols=colIdx-1;
2125 }
2126 m_numCols = maxCols;
2127}

2129//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
2130
2131int DocHtmlDescTitle::parse(DocNodeVariant *thisVariant)
2132{
2133 int retval=0;
2134 auto ns = AutoNodeStack(parser(),thisVariant);
2135 DBG(("DocHtmlDescTitle::parse() start\n"));
2136
2137 int tok;
2138 while ((tok=parser()->tokenizer.lex()))
2139 {
2140 if (!parser()->defaultHandleToken(thisVariant,tok,children()))
2141 {
2142 const char *cmd_start = "\\";
2143 switch (tok)
2144 {
2145 case TK_COMMAND_AT:
2146 cmd_start = "@";
2147 // fall through
2148 case TK_COMMAND_BS:
2149 {
2150 QCString cmdName=parser()->context.token->name;
2151 bool isJavaLink=FALSE;
2152 switch (Mappers::cmdMapper->map(cmdName))
2153 {
2154 case CMD_REF:
2155 {
2156 tok=parser()->tokenizer.lex();
2157 if (tok!=TK_WHITESPACE)
2158 {
2159 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"expected whitespace after \\%s command",
2160 qPrint(parser()->context.token->name));
2161 }
2162 else
2163 {
2164 parser()->tokenizer.setStateRef();
2165 tok=parser()->tokenizer.lex(); // get the reference id
2166 if (tok!=TK_WORD)
2167 {
2168 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"unexpected token %s as the argument of \\%s command",
2169 DocTokenizer::tokToString(tok),qPrint(cmdName));
2170 }
2171 else
2172 {
2173 auto vDocRef = children().append<DocRef>(parser(),thisVariant,parser()->context.token->name,parser()->context.context);
2174 children().get_last<DocRef>()->parse(vDocRef);
2175 }
2176 parser()->tokenizer.setStatePara();
2177 }
2178 }
2179 break;
2180 case CMD_JAVALINK:
2181 isJavaLink=TRUE;
2182 // fall through
2183 case CMD_LINK:
2184 {
2185 tok=parser()->tokenizer.lex();
2186 if (tok!=TK_WHITESPACE)
2187 {
2188 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"expected whitespace after \\%s command",
2189 qPrint(cmdName));
2190 }
2191 else
2192 {
2193 parser()->tokenizer.setStateLink();
2194 tok=parser()->tokenizer.lex();
2195 if (tok!=TK_WORD)
2196 {
2197 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"unexpected token %s as the argument of \\%s command",
2198 DocTokenizer::tokToString(tok),qPrint(cmdName));
2199 }
2200 else
2201 {
2202 parser()->tokenizer.setStatePara();
2203 auto vDocLink = children().append<DocLink>(parser(),thisVariant,parser()->context.token->name);
2204 DocLink *lnk = children().get_last<DocLink>();
2205 QCString leftOver = lnk->parse(vDocLink,isJavaLink);
2206 if (!leftOver.isEmpty())
2207 {
2208 children().append<DocWord>(parser(),thisVariant,leftOver);
2209 }
2210 }
2211 }
2212 }
2213
2214 break;
2215 default:
2216 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"Illegal command %s found as part of a <dt> tag",
2217 qPrint(cmd_start + parser()->context.token->name));
2218 }
2219 }
2220 break;
2221 case TK_SYMBOL:
2222 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"Unsupported symbol \\%s found as part of a <dt> tag",
2223 qPrint(parser()->context.token->name));
2224 break;
2225 case TK_HTMLTAG:
2226 {
2227 int tagId=Mappers::htmlTagMapper->map(parser()->context.token->name);
2228 if (tagId==HTML_DD && !parser()->context.token->endTag) // found <dd> tag
2229 {
2230 retval = RetVal_DescData;
2231 goto endtitle;
2232 }
2233 else if (tagId==HTML_DT && parser()->context.token->endTag)
2234 {
2235 // ignore </dt> tag.
2236 }
2237 else if (tagId==HTML_DT)
2238 {
2239 // missing <dt> tag.
2240 retval = RetVal_DescTitle;
2241 goto endtitle;
2242 }
2243 else if (tagId==HTML_DL && parser()->context.token->endTag)
2244 {
2245 retval=RetVal_EndDesc;
2246 goto endtitle;
2247 }
2248 else if (tagId==HTML_A)
2249 {
2250 if (!parser()->context.token->endTag)
2251 {
2252 parser()->handleAHref(thisVariant,children(),parser()->context.token->attribs);
2253 }
2254 }
2255 else
2256 {
2257 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"Unexpected html tag <%s%s> found within <dt> context",
2258 parser()->context.token->endTag?"/":"",qPrint(parser()->context.token->name));
2259 }
2260 }
2261 break;
2262 default:
2263 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"Unexpected token %s found as part of a <dt> tag",
2264 DocTokenizer::tokToString(tok));
2265 break;
2266 }
2267 }
2268 }
2269 if (tok==0)
2270 {
2271 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"Unexpected end of comment while inside"
2272 " <dt> tag");
2273 }
2274endtitle:
2275 parser()->handlePendingStyleCommands(thisVariant,children());
2276 DBG(("DocHtmlDescTitle::parse() end\n"));
2277 return retval;
2278}

2736//--------------------------------------------------------------------------
2737
2738void DocTitle::parse(DocNodeVariant *thisVariant)
2739{
2740 DBG(("DocTitle::parse() start\n"));
2741 auto ns = AutoNodeStack(parser(),thisVariant);
2742 parser()->tokenizer.setStateTitle();
2743 int tok;
2744 while ((tok=parser()->tokenizer.lex()))
2745 {
2746 if (!parser()->defaultHandleToken(thisVariant,tok,children()))
2747 {
2748 parser()->errorHandleDefaultToken(thisVariant,tok,children(),"title section");
2749 }

2913int DocParamList::parse(DocNodeVariant *thisVariant,const QCString &cmdName)
2914{
2915 int retval=RetVal_OK;
2916 DBG(("DocParamList::parse() start\n"));
2917 auto ns = AutoNodeStack(parser(),thisVariant);
2918 DocNodeVariant *vDocPara = 0;
2919 DocPara *par=0;
2920 QCString saveCmdName = cmdName;
2921
2922 int tok=parser()->tokenizer.lex();
2923 if (tok!=TK_WHITESPACE)
2924 {
2925 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"expected whitespace after \\%s command",
2926 qPrint(saveCmdName));
2927 retval=RetVal_EndParBlock;
2928 goto endparamlist;
2929 }
2930 parser()->tokenizer.setStateParam();
2931 tok=parser()->tokenizer.lex();
2932 while (tok==TK_WORD) /* there is a parameter name */
2933 {
2934 if (m_type==DocParamSect::Param)
2935 {
2936 int typeSeparator = parser()->context.token->name.find('#'); // explicit type position
2937 if (typeSeparator!=-1)
2938 {
2939 parser()->handleParameterType(thisVariant,m_paramTypes,parser()->context.token->name.left(typeSeparator));
2940 parser()->context.token->name = parser()->context.token->name.mid(typeSeparator+1);
2941 parser()->context.hasParamCommand=TRUE;
2942 parser()->checkArgumentName();
2943 if (parent() && std::holds_alternative<DocParamSect>(*parent()))
2944 {
2945 std::get<DocParamSect>(*parent()).m_hasTypeSpecifier=true;
2946 }
2947 }
2948 else
2949 {
2950 parser()->context.hasParamCommand=TRUE;
2951 parser()->checkArgumentName();
2952 }
2953 }
2954 else if (m_type==DocParamSect::RetVal)
2955 {
2956 parser()->context.hasReturnCommand=TRUE;
2957 parser()->checkRetvalName();
2958 }
2959 //m_params.append(parser()->context.token->name);
2960 parser()->handleLinkedWord(thisVariant,m_params);
2961 tok=parser()->tokenizer.lex();
2962 }
2963 parser()->tokenizer.setStatePara();
2964 if (tok==0) /* premature end of comment block */
2965 {
2966 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"unexpected end of comment block while parsing the "
2967 "argument of command %s",qPrint(saveCmdName));
2968 retval=RetVal_EndParBlock;
2969 goto endparamlist;
2970 }
2971 if (tok!=TK_WHITESPACE) /* premature end of comment block */
2972 {
2973 if (tok!=TK_NEWPARA) /* empty param description */
2974 {
2975 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"unexpected token %s in comment block while parsing the "
2976 "argument of command %s",DocTokenizer::tokToString(tok),qPrint(saveCmdName));
2977 }
2978 retval=RetVal_EndParBlock;
2979 goto endparamlist;
2980 }
2981
2982 vDocPara = m_paragraphs.append<DocPara>(parser(),thisVariant);
2983 par = m_paragraphs.get_last<DocPara>();
2984 retval = par->parse(vDocPara);
2985 par->markFirst();
2986 par->markLast();
2987
2988endparamlist:
2989 DBG(("DocParamList::parse() end retval=%d\n",retval));
2990 return retval;
2991}

2993int DocParamList::parseXml(DocNodeVariant *thisVariant,const QCString &paramName)
2994{
2995 int retval=RetVal_OK;
2996 DBG(("DocParamList::parseXml() start\n"));
2997 auto ns = AutoNodeStack(parser(),thisVariant);
2998
2999 parser()->context.token->name = paramName;
3000 if (m_type==DocParamSect::Param)
3001 {
3002 parser()->context.hasParamCommand=TRUE;
3003 parser()->checkArgumentName();
3004 }
3005 else if (m_type==DocParamSect::RetVal)
3006 {
3007 parser()->context.hasReturnCommand=TRUE;
3008 parser()->checkRetvalName();
3009 }
3010
3011 parser()->handleLinkedWord(thisVariant,m_params);
3012
3013 do
3014 {
3015 auto vDocPara = m_paragraphs.append<DocPara>(parser(),thisVariant);
3016 DocPara *par = m_paragraphs.get_last<DocPara>();
3017 retval = par->parse(vDocPara);
3018 if (par->isEmpty()) // avoid adding an empty paragraph for the whitespace
3019 // after </para> and before </param>
3020 {
3021 m_paragraphs.pop_back();
3022 break;
3023 }
3024 else // append the paragraph to the list
3025 {
3026 if (!m_paragraphs.empty())
3027 {
3028 m_paragraphs.get_last<DocPara>()->markLast(FALSE);
3029 }
3030 bool markFirst = m_paragraphs.empty();
3031 par = &std::get<DocPara>(m_paragraphs.back());
3032 if (markFirst)
3033 {
3034 par->markFirst();
3035 }
3036 par->markLast();
3037 }
3038
3039 if (retval == 0) break;
3040
3041 } while (retval==RetVal_CloseXml &&
3042 Mappers::htmlTagMapper->map(parser()->context.token->name)!=XML_PARAM &&
3043 Mappers::htmlTagMapper->map(parser()->context.token->name)!=XML_TYPEPARAM &&
3044 Mappers::htmlTagMapper->map(parser()->context.token->name)!=XML_EXCEPTION);
3045
3046
3047 if (retval==0) /* premature end of comment block */
3048 {
3049 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"unterminated param or exception tag");
3050 }
3051 else
3052 {
3053 retval=RetVal_OK;
3054 }
3055
3056 DBG(("DocParamList::parse() end retval=%d\n",retval));
3057 return retval;
3058}

3249void DocPara::handleShowDate(DocNodeVariant *thisVariant)
3250{
3251 DBG(("handleShowDate()\n"));
3252 QCString fmt;
3253 QCString date;
3254 int tok=parser()->tokenizer.lex();
3255 if (tok!=TK_WHITESPACE)
3256 {
3257 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"expected whitespace after '\\%s' command",
3258 qPrint("showdate"));
3259 return;
3260 }
3261 parser()->tokenizer.setStateQuotedString();
3262 tok = parser()->tokenizer.lex();
3263 if (tok!=TK_WORD)
3264 {
3265 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"invalid <format> argument for command '\\showdate'");
3266 parser()->tokenizer.setStatePara();
3267 return;

3269 fmt = parser()->context.token->name;
3270
3271 parser()->tokenizer.setStateShowDate();
3272 tok = parser()->tokenizer.lex();
3273
3274 QCString specDate = parser()->context.token->name.stripWhiteSpace();
3275 if (!specDate.isEmpty() && tok!=TK_WORD)
3276 {
3277 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"invalid <date_time> argument for command '\\showdate'");
3278 parser()->tokenizer.setStatePara();
3279 return;

3282 std::tm dat{};

3284 QCString err = dateTimeFromString(specDate,dat,specFormat);
3285 if (!err.isEmpty())
3286 {

3288 parser()->tokenizer.setStatePara();
3289 return;

3291
3292 int usedFormat=0;
3293 QCString dateTimeStr = formatDateTime(fmt,dat,usedFormat);
3294
3295 // warn the user if the format contains markers that are not explicitly filled in
3296 for (int i=0;i<SF_NumBits;i++)

3300 {

3302 qPrint(fmt),SF_bit2str(i),qPrint(specDate),SF_bit2str(i));
3303 }
3304 }

3306 children().append<DocWord>(parser(),thisVariant,dateTimeStr);
3307 parser()->tokenizer.setStatePara();

3408 qPrint(saveCmdName));
3409 return;

3417 DocTokenizer::tokToString(tok),qPrint(saveCmdName));
3418 return;
3419 }

3422 parser()->context.context,
3423 parser()->context.fileName,
3424 parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr());

3428 children().pop_back();
3429 }

3505
3506void DocPara::handleInclude(DocNodeVariant *thisVariant,const QCString &cmdName,DocInclude::Type t)
3507{
3508 DBG(("handleInclude(%s)\n",qPrint(cmdName)));
3509 QCString saveCmdName = cmdName;
3510 int tok=parser()->tokenizer.lex();
3511 bool isBlock = false;
3512 if (tok==TK_WORD && parser()->context.token->name=="{")
3513 {
3514 parser()->tokenizer.setStateOptions();
3515 tok=parser()->tokenizer.lex();
3516 parser()->tokenizer.setStatePara();
3517 StringVector optList=split(parser()->context.token->name.str(),",");
3518 auto contains = [&optList](const char *kw)
3519 {
3520 return std::find(optList.begin(),optList.end(),kw)!=optList.end();
3521 };
3522 if (t==DocInclude::Include && contains("lineno"))
3523 {
3524 t = DocInclude::IncWithLines;
3525 }
3526 else if (t==DocInclude::Snippet && contains("lineno"))
3527 {
3528 t = DocInclude::SnipWithLines;
3529 }
3530 else if (t==DocInclude::DontInclude && contains("lineno"))
3531 {
3532 t = DocInclude::DontIncWithLines;
3533 }
3534 else if (t==DocInclude::Include && contains("doc"))
3535 {
3536 t = DocInclude::IncludeDoc;
3537 }
3538 else if (t==DocInclude::Snippet && contains("doc"))
3539 {
3540 t = DocInclude::SnippetDoc;
3541 }
3542 tok=parser()->tokenizer.lex();
3543 if (tok!=TK_WHITESPACE)
3544 {
3545 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"expected whitespace after \\%s command",
3546 qPrint(saveCmdName));
3547 return;
3548 }
3549 }
3550 else if (tok==TK_WORD && parser()->context.token->name=="[")
3551 {
3552 parser()->tokenizer.setStateBlock();
3553 tok=parser()->tokenizer.lex();
3554 isBlock = (parser()->context.token->name.stripWhiteSpace() == "block");
3555 parser()->tokenizer.setStatePara();
3556 tok=parser()->tokenizer.lex();
3557 }
3558 else if (tok!=TK_WHITESPACE)
3559 {
3560 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"expected whitespace after \\%s command",
3561 qPrint(saveCmdName));
3562 return;
3563 }
3564 parser()->tokenizer.setStateFile();
3565 tok=parser()->tokenizer.lex();
3566 parser()->tokenizer.setStatePara();
3567 if (tok==0)
3568 {
3569 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"unexpected end of comment block while parsing the "
3570 "argument of command %s",qPrint(saveCmdName));
3571 return;
3572 }
3573 else if (tok!=TK_WORD)
3574 {
3575 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"unexpected token %s as the argument of %s",
3576 DocTokenizer::tokToString(tok),qPrint(saveCmdName));
3577 return;
3578 }
3579 QCString fileName = parser()->context.token->name;
3580 QCString blockId;
3581 if (t==DocInclude::Snippet || t==DocInclude::SnipWithLines || t==DocInclude::SnippetDoc)
3582 {
3583 if (fileName == "this") fileName=parser()->context.fileName;
3584 parser()->tokenizer.setStateSnippet();
3585 tok=parser()->tokenizer.lex();
3586 parser()->tokenizer.setStatePara();
3587 if (tok!=TK_WORD)
3588 {
3589 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"expected block identifier, but found token %s instead while parsing the %s command",
3590 DocTokenizer::tokToString(tok),qPrint(saveCmdName));
3591 return;
3592 }
3593 blockId = "["+parser()->context.token->name+"]";
3594 }
3595
3596 // This is the only place to handle the \includedoc and \snippetdoc commands,
3597 // as the content is included here as if it is really here.
3598 if (t==DocInclude::IncludeDoc || t==DocInclude::SnippetDoc)
3599 {
3600 QCString inc_text;
3601 int inc_line = 1;
3602 parser()->readTextFileByName(fileName,inc_text);
3603 if (t==DocInclude::SnippetDoc)
3604 {
3605 int count;
3606 if (!blockId.isEmpty() && (count=inc_text.contains(blockId.data()))!=2)
3607 {
3608 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"block marked with %s for \\snippet should appear twice in file %s, found it %d times\n",
3609 qPrint(blockId),qPrint(fileName),count);
3610 }
3611 inc_line = lineBlock(inc_text, blockId);
3612 inc_text = extractBlock(inc_text, blockId);
3613 }
3614
3615 Markdown markdown(fileName,inc_line);
3616 QCString strippedDoc = stripIndentation(inc_text);
3617 QCString processedDoc = Config_getBool(MARKDOWN_SUPPORT) ? markdown.process(strippedDoc,inc_line) : strippedDoc;
3618
3619 parser()->pushContext();
3620 parser()->context.fileName = fileName;
3621 parser()->tokenizer.setLineNr(inc_line);
3622 parser()->internalValidatingParseDoc(thisVariant,children(),processedDoc);
3623 parser()->popContext();
3624 }
3625 else
3626 {
3627 auto vDocInclude = children().append<DocInclude>(parser(),thisVariant,fileName,
3628 parser()->context.context,t,
3629 parser()->context.isExample,
3630 parser()->context.exampleName,
3631 blockId,isBlock);
3632 children().get_last<DocInclude>()->parse(vDocInclude);
3633 }
3634}

3636void DocPara::handleSection(DocNodeVariant *,const QCString &cmdName)
3637{
3638 QCString saveCmdName = cmdName;
3639 // get the argument of the section command.
3640 int tok=parser()->tokenizer.lex();
3641 if (tok!=TK_WHITESPACE)
3642 {
3643 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"expected whitespace after \\%s command",
3644 qPrint(saveCmdName));
3645 return;
3646 }
3647 tok=parser()->tokenizer.lex();
3648 if (tok==0)
3649 {
3650 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"unexpected end of comment block while parsing the "
3651 "argument of command %s\n", qPrint(saveCmdName));
3652 return;
3653 }
3654 else if (tok!=TK_WORD && tok!=TK_LNKWORD)
3655 {

3661 parser()->tokenizer.setStateSkipTitle();
3662 parser()->tokenizer.lex();
3663 parser()->tokenizer.setStatePara();
3664}

3682
3683int DocPara::handleStartCode(DocNodeVariant *thisVariant)
3684{
3685 int retval = parser()->tokenizer.lex();
3686 QCString lang = parser()->context.token->name;
3687 if (!lang.isEmpty() && lang.at(0)!='.')
3688 {
3689 lang="."+lang;
3690 }
3691 if (parser()->context.xmlComment)
3692 {
3693 parser()->context.token->verb = substitute(substitute(parser()->context.token->verb,"&lt;","<"),"&gt;",">");
3694 }
3695 // search for the first non-whitespace line, index is stored in li
3696 int i=0,li=0,l=parser()->context.token->verb.length();
3697 while (i<l && (parser()->context.token->verb.at(i)==' ' || parser()->context.token->verb.at(i)=='\n'))
3698 {
3699 if (parser()->context.token->verb.at(i)=='\n') li=i+1;
3700 i++;
3701 }
3702 children().append<DocVerbatim>(parser(),thisVariant,
3703 parser()->context.context,
3704 stripIndentation(parser()->context.token->verb.mid(li)),
3705 DocVerbatim::Code,
3706 parser()->context.isExample,
3707 parser()->context.exampleName,
3708 FALSE,lang);
3709 if (retval==0) warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"code section ended without end marker");
3710 parser()->tokenizer.setStatePara();
3711 return retval;
3712}

3714void DocPara::handleInheritDoc(DocNodeVariant *thisVariant)
3715{
3716 if (parser()->context.memberDef) // inheriting docs from a member
3717 {
3718 const MemberDef *reMd = parser()->context.memberDef->reimplements();
3719 if (reMd) // member from which was inherited.
3720 {
3721 const MemberDef *thisMd = parser()->context.memberDef;
3722 //printf("{InheritDocs:%s=>%s}\n",qPrint(parser()->context.memberDef->qualifiedName()),qPrint(reMd->qualifiedName()));
3723 parser()->pushContext();
3724 parser()->context.scope=reMd->getOuterScope();
3725 if (parser()->context.scope!=Doxygen::globalScope)
3726 {
3727 parser()->context.context=parser()->context.scope->name();
3728 }
3729 parser()->context.memberDef=reMd;
3730 while (!parser()->context.styleStack.empty()) parser()->context.styleStack.pop();
3731 while (!parser()->context.nodeStack.empty()) parser()->context.nodeStack.pop();
3732 parser()->context.copyStack.push_back(reMd);
3733 parser()->internalValidatingParseDoc(thisVariant,children(),reMd->briefDescription());
3734 parser()->internalValidatingParseDoc(thisVariant,children(),reMd->documentation());
3735 parser()->context.copyStack.pop_back();
3736 auto hasParamCommand = parser()->context.hasParamCommand;
3737 auto hasReturnCommand = parser()->context.hasReturnCommand;
3738 auto retvalsFound = parser()->context.retvalsFound;
3739 auto paramsFound = parser()->context.paramsFound;
3740 parser()->popContext();
3741 parser()->context.hasParamCommand = hasParamCommand;
3742 parser()->context.hasReturnCommand = hasReturnCommand;
3743 parser()->context.retvalsFound = retvalsFound;
3744 parser()->context.paramsFound = paramsFound;
3745 parser()->context.memberDef = thisMd;
3746 }
3747 }

3751int DocPara::handleCommand(DocNodeVariant *thisVariant,const QCString &cmdName, const int tok)
3752{
3753 DBG(("handleCommand(%s)\n",qPrint(cmdName)));
3754 int retval = RetVal_OK;
3755 int cmdId = Mappers::cmdMapper->map(cmdName);
3756 switch (cmdId)
3757 {
3758 case CMD_UNKNOWN:
3759 children().append<DocWord>(parser(),thisVariant,TK_COMMAND_CHAR(tok) + cmdName);
3760 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"Found unknown command '%s%s'",TK_COMMAND_CHAR(tok),qPrint(cmdName));
3761 break;
3762 case CMD_EMPHASIS:
3763 children().append<DocStyleChange>(parser(),thisVariant,parser()->context.nodeStack.size(),DocStyleChange::Italic,cmdName,TRUE);
3764 retval=parser()->handleStyleArgument(thisVariant,children(),cmdName);

3766 if (retval!=TK_WORD) children().append<DocWhiteSpace>(parser(),thisVariant," ");
3767 break;
3768 case CMD_BOLD:
3769 children().append<DocStyleChange>(parser(),thisVariant,parser()->context.nodeStack.size(),DocStyleChange::Bold,cmdName,TRUE);
3770 retval=parser()->handleStyleArgument(thisVariant,children(),cmdName);
3771 children().append<DocStyleChange>(parser(),thisVariant,parser()->context.nodeStack.size(),DocStyleChange::Bold,cmdName,FALSE);
3772 if (retval!=TK_WORD) children().append<DocWhiteSpace>(parser(),thisVariant," ");
3773 break;
3774 case CMD_CODE:
3775 children().append<DocStyleChange>(parser(),thisVariant,parser()->context.nodeStack.size(),DocStyleChange::Code,cmdName,TRUE);
3776 retval=parser()->handleStyleArgument(thisVariant,children(),cmdName);
3777 children().append<DocStyleChange>(parser(),thisVariant,parser()->context.nodeStack.size(),DocStyleChange::Code,cmdName,FALSE);
3778 if (retval!=TK_WORD) children().append<DocWhiteSpace>(parser(),thisVariant," ");
3779 break;
3780 case CMD_BSLASH:
3781 children().append<DocSymbol>(parser(),thisVariant,HtmlEntityMapper::Sym_BSlash);

3783 case CMD_AT:
3784 children().append<DocSymbol>(parser(),thisVariant,HtmlEntityMapper::Sym_At);
3785 break;

3787 children().append<DocSymbol>(parser(),thisVariant,HtmlEntityMapper::Sym_Less);

4412static bool findAttribute(const HtmlAttribList &tagHtmlAttribs,
4413 const char *attrName,
4414 QCString *result)
4415{
4416
4417 for (const auto &opt : tagHtmlAttribs)
4418 {
4419 if (opt.name==attrName)
4420 {
4421 *result = opt.value;
4422 return TRUE;
4423 }
4424 }
4425 return FALSE;
4426}

4428int DocPara::handleHtmlStartTag(DocNodeVariant *thisVariant,const QCString &tagName,const HtmlAttribList &tagHtmlAttribs)
4429{
4430 DBG(("handleHtmlStartTag(%s,%d)\n",qPrint(tagName),tagHtmlAttribs.size()));
4431 int retval=RetVal_OK;
4432 int tagId = Mappers::htmlTagMapper->map(tagName);
4433 if (parser()->context.token->emptyTag && !(tagId&XML_CmdMask) &&
4434 tagId!=HTML_UNKNOWN && tagId!=HTML_IMG && tagId!=HTML_BR && tagId!=HTML_HR && tagId!=HTML_P
4435 && tagId!=HTML_DIV && tagId!=HTML_SPAN)
4436 {
4437 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"HTML tag ('<%s/>') may not use the 'empty tag' XHTML syntax.",
4438 qPrint(tagName));
4439 }
4440 switch (tagId)
4441 {
4442 case HTML_UL:
4443 if (!parser()->context.token->emptyTag)
4444 {
4445 auto vDocHtmlList = children().append<DocHtmlList>(parser(),thisVariant,
4446 tagHtmlAttribs,DocHtmlList::Unordered);
4447 retval=children().get_last<DocHtmlList>()->parse(vDocHtmlList);
4448 }
4449 break;
4450 case HTML_OL:
4451 if (!parser()->context.token->emptyTag)
4452 {
4453 auto vDocHtmlList = children().append<DocHtmlList>(parser(),thisVariant,
4454 tagHtmlAttribs,DocHtmlList::Ordered);
4455 retval=children().get_last<DocHtmlList>()->parse(vDocHtmlList);
4456 }
4457 break;
4458 case HTML_LI:
4459 if (parser()->context.token->emptyTag) break;
4460 if (!insideUL(thisVariant) && !insideOL(thisVariant))
4461 {
4462 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"lonely <li> tag found");
4463 }
4464 else
4465 {
4466 retval=RetVal_ListItem;
4467 }
4468 break;
4469 case HTML_BOLD:
4470 if (!parser()->context.token->emptyTag) parser()->handleStyleEnter(thisVariant,children(),DocStyleChange::Bold,tagName,&parser()->context.token->attribs);
4471 break;
4472 case HTML_S:
4473 if (!parser()->context.token->emptyTag) parser()->handleStyleEnter(thisVariant,children(),DocStyleChange::S,tagName,&parser()->context.token->attribs);
4474 break;
4475 case HTML_STRIKE:
4476 if (!parser()->context.token->emptyTag) parser()->handleStyleEnter(thisVariant,children(),DocStyleChange::Strike,tagName,&parser()->context.token->attribs);
4477 break;
4478 case HTML_DEL:
4479 if (!parser()->context.token->emptyTag) parser()->handleStyleEnter(thisVariant,children(),DocStyleChange::Del,tagName,&parser()->context.token->attribs);
4480 break;
4481 case HTML_UNDERLINE:
4482 if (!parser()->context.token->emptyTag) parser()->handleStyleEnter(thisVariant,children(),DocStyleChange::Underline,tagName,&parser()->context.token->attribs);
4483 break;
4484 case HTML_INS:
4485 if (!parser()->context.token->emptyTag) parser()->handleStyleEnter(thisVariant,children(),DocStyleChange::Ins,tagName,&parser()->context.token->attribs);
4486 break;
4487 case HTML_CODE:
4488 if (parser()->context.token->emptyTag) break;
4489 if (/*getLanguageFromFileName(parser()->context.fileName)==SrcLangExt_CSharp ||*/ parser()->context.xmlComment)
4490 // for C# source or inside a <summary> or <remark> section we

4501 case HTML_EMPHASIS:

4504 case HTML_DIV:

4514 break;
4515 case HTML_SUP:

4517 break;
4518 case HTML_CENTER:

4521 case HTML_SMALL:

4523 break;
4524 case HTML_CITE:

4526 break;
4527 case HTML_PRE:
