4593 case HTML_H5:
4594 if (!parser()->context.token->emptyTag) retval=handleHtmlHeader(thisVariant,tagHtmlAttribs,5);
4595 break;
4596 case HTML_H6:
4597 if (!parser()->context.token->emptyTag) retval=handleHtmlHeader(thisVariant,tagHtmlAttribs,6);
4598 break;
4599 case HTML_IMG:
4600 {
4601 parser()->handleImg(thisVariant,children(),tagHtmlAttribs);
4602 }
4603 break;
4604 case HTML_DETAILS:
4605 if (!parser()->context.token->emptyTag)
4606 {
4607 auto vDocHtmlDetails = children().append<DocHtmlDetails>(parser(),thisVariant,
4608 tagHtmlAttribs);
4609 retval=children().get_last<DocHtmlDetails>()->parse(vDocHtmlDetails);
4610 }
4611 break;
4612 case HTML_BLOCKQUOTE:
4613 if (!parser()->context.token->emptyTag)
4614 {
4615 auto vDocHtmlBlockQuote = children().append<DocHtmlBlockQuote>(parser(),thisVariant,tagHtmlAttribs);
4616 retval = children().get_last<DocHtmlBlockQuote>()->parse(vDocHtmlBlockQuote);
4617 }
4618 break;
4619
4620 case XML_SUMMARY:
4621 if (insideDetails(thisVariant))
4622 {
4623 if (!parser()->context.token->emptyTag)
4624 {
4625 DocNodeVariant *n=parent();
4626 while (n && !std::holds_alternative<DocHtmlDetails>(*n)) n=::parent(n);
4627 DocHtmlDetails *d = std::get_if<DocHtmlDetails>(n);
4628 if (d)
4629 {
4630 if (!d->summary()) // details section does not have a summary yet
4631 {
4632 d->parseSummary(n,parser()->context.token->attribs);
4633 }
4634 else
4635 {
4636 retval = TK_NEWPARA;
4637 }
4638 }
4639 }
4640 }
4641 break;
4642 case XML_REMARKS:
4643 case XML_EXAMPLE:
4644 parser()->context.xmlComment=TRUE;
4645 // fall through
4646 case XML_VALUE:
4647 case XML_PARA:
4648 if (!children().empty())
4649 {
4650 retval = TK_NEWPARA;
4651 }
4652 break;
4653 case XML_DESCRIPTION:
4654 if (insideTable(thisVariant))
4655 {
4656 retval=RetVal_TableCell;
4657 }
4658 break;
4659 case XML_C:
4660 parser()->handleStyleEnter(thisVariant,children(),DocStyleChange::Code,tagName,&parser()->context.token->attribs);
4661 break;
4662 case XML_PARAM:
4663 case XML_TYPEPARAM:
4664 {
4665 parser()->context.xmlComment=TRUE;
4666 QCString paramName;
4667 if (findAttribute(tagHtmlAttribs,"name",&paramName))
4668 {
4669 if (paramName.isEmpty())
4670 {
4671 if (Config_getBool(WARN_NO_PARAMDOC))
4672 {
4673 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"empty 'name' attribute for <param%s> tag.",tagId==XML_PARAM?"":"type");
4674 }
4675 }
4676 else
4677 {
4678 retval = handleParamSection(thisVariant, paramName,
4679 tagId==XML_PARAM ? DocParamSect::Param : DocParamSect::TemplateParam,
4680 TRUE);
4681 }
4682 }
4683 else
4684 {
4685 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"Missing 'name' attribute from <param%s> tag.",tagId==XML_PARAM?"":"type");
4686 }
4687 }
4688 break;
4689 case XML_PARAMREF:
4690 case XML_TYPEPARAMREF:
4691 {
4692 QCString paramName;
4693 if (findAttribute(tagHtmlAttribs,"name",&paramName))
4694 {
4695 //printf("paramName=%s\n",qPrint(paramName));
4696 children().append<DocStyleChange>(parser(),thisVariant,parser()->context.nodeStack.size(),DocStyleChange::Italic,tagName,TRUE);
4697 children().append<DocWord>(parser(),thisVariant,paramName);
4698 children().append<DocStyleChange>(parser(),thisVariant,parser()->context.nodeStack.size(),DocStyleChange::Italic,tagName,FALSE);
4699 if (retval!=TK_WORD) children().append<DocWhiteSpace>(parser(),thisVariant," ");
4700 }
4701 else
4702 {
4703 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"Missing 'name' attribute from <param%sref> tag.",tagId==XML_PARAMREF?"":"type");
4704 }
4705 }
4706 break;
4707 case XML_EXCEPTION:
4708 {
4709 parser()->context.xmlComment=TRUE;
4710 QCString exceptName;
4711 if (findAttribute(tagHtmlAttribs,"cref",&exceptName))
4712 {
4713 unescapeCRef(exceptName);
4714 retval = handleParamSection(thisVariant,exceptName,DocParamSect::Exception,TRUE);
4715 }
4716 else
4717 {
4718 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"Missing 'cref' attribute from <exception> tag.");
4719 }
4720 }
4721 break;
4722 case XML_ITEM:
4723 case XML_LISTHEADER:
4724 if (insideTable(thisVariant))
4725 {
4726 retval=RetVal_TableRow;
4727 }
4728 else if (insideUL(thisVariant) || insideOL(thisVariant))
4729 {
4730 retval=RetVal_ListItem;
4731 }
4732 else
4733 {
4734 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"lonely <item> tag found");
4735 }
4736 break;
4737 case XML_RETURNS:
4738 parser()->context.xmlComment=TRUE;
4739 retval = handleSimpleSection(thisVariant,DocSimpleSect::Return,TRUE);
4740 parser()->context.hasReturnCommand=TRUE;
4741 break;
4742 case XML_TERM:
4743 //children().push_back(std::make_unique<DocStyleChange>(this,parser()->context.nodeStack.size(),DocStyleChange::Bold,TRUE));
4744 if (insideTable(thisVariant))
4745 {
4746 retval=RetVal_TableCell;
4747 }
4748 break;
4749 case XML_SEE:
4750 // I'm not sure if <see> is the same as <seealso> or if it
4751 // should you link a member without producing a section. The
4752 // C# specification is extremely vague about this (but what else
4753 // can we expect from Microsoft...)
4754 {
4755 QCString cref;
4756 //printf("XML_SEE: empty tag=%d\n",parser()->context.token->emptyTag);
4757 if (findAttribute(tagHtmlAttribs,"cref",&cref))
4758 {
4759 unescapeCRef(cref);
4760 if (parser()->context.token->emptyTag) // <see cref="..."/> style
4761 {
4762 bool inSeeBlock = parser()->context.inSeeBlock;
4763 parser()->context.token->name = cref;
4764 parser()->context.inSeeBlock = TRUE;
4765 parser()->handleLinkedWord(thisVariant,children(),TRUE);
4766 parser()->context.inSeeBlock = inSeeBlock;
4767 }
4768 else // <see cref="...">...</see> style
4769 {
4770 //DocRef *ref = new DocRef(this,cref);
4771 //children().append(ref);
4772 //ref->parse();
4773 parser()->tokenizer.setStatePara();
4774 auto vDocLink = children().append<DocLink>(parser(),thisVariant,cref);
4775 DocLink *lnk = children().get_last<DocLink>();
4776 QCString leftOver = lnk->parse(vDocLink,FALSE,TRUE);
4777 if (!leftOver.isEmpty())
4778 {
4779 children().append<DocWord>(parser(),thisVariant,leftOver);
4780 }
4781 }
4782 }
4783 else if (findAttribute(tagHtmlAttribs,"langword",&cref)) // <see langword="..."/> or <see langword="..."></see>
4784 {
4785 bool inSeeBlock = parser()->context.inSeeBlock;
4786 parser()->context.token->name = cref;
4787 parser()->context.inSeeBlock = TRUE;
4788 children().append<DocStyleChange>(parser(),thisVariant,parser()->context.nodeStack.size(),DocStyleChange::Code,tagName,TRUE);
4789 parser()->handleLinkedWord(thisVariant,children(),TRUE);
4790 children().append<DocStyleChange>(parser(),thisVariant,parser()->context.nodeStack.size(),DocStyleChange::Code,tagName,FALSE);
4791 parser()->context.inSeeBlock = inSeeBlock;
4792 }
4793 else
4794 {
4795 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"Missing 'cref' or 'langword' attribute from <see> tag.");
4796 }
4797 }
4798 break;
4799 case XML_SEEALSO:
4800 {
4801 parser()->context.xmlComment=TRUE;
4802 QCString cref;
4803 if (findAttribute(tagHtmlAttribs,"cref",&cref))
4804 {
4805 unescapeCRef(cref);
4806 // Look for an existing "see" section
4807 DocNodeVariant *vss=0;
4808 for (auto &n : children())
4809 {
4810 DocSimpleSect *candidate = std::get_if<DocSimpleSect>(&n);
4811 if (candidate && candidate->type()==DocSimpleSect::See)
4812 {
4813 vss = &n;
4814 }
4815 }
4816
4817 if (!vss) // start new section
4818 {
4819 vss = children().append<DocSimpleSect>(parser(),thisVariant,DocSimpleSect::See);
4820 }
4821
4822 std::get<DocSimpleSect>(*vss).appendLinkWord(vss,cref);
4823 retval = RetVal_OK;
4824 }
4825 else
4826 {
4827 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"Missing 'cref' attribute from <seealso> tag.");
4828 }
4829 }
4830 break;
4831 case XML_LIST:
4832 {
4833 QCString type;
4834 findAttribute(tagHtmlAttribs,"type",&type);
4835 DocHtmlList::Type listType = DocHtmlList::Unordered;
4836 HtmlAttribList emptyList;
4837 if (type=="number")
4838 {
4839 listType=DocHtmlList::Ordered;
4840 }
4841 if (type=="table")
4842 {
4843 auto vDocHtmlTable = children().append<DocHtmlTable>(parser(),thisVariant,emptyList);
4844 retval=children().get_last<DocHtmlTable>()->parseXml(vDocHtmlTable);
4845 }
4846 else
4847 {
4848 auto vHtmlList = children().append<DocHtmlList>(parser(),thisVariant,emptyList,listType);
4849 retval=children().get_last<DocHtmlList>()->parseXml(vHtmlList);
4850 }
4851 }
4852 break;
4853 case XML_INCLUDE:
4854 case XML_PERMISSION:
4855 // These tags are defined in .Net but are currently unsupported
4856 parser()->context.xmlComment=TRUE;
4857 break;
4858 case HTML_UNKNOWN:
4859 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"Unsupported xml/html tag <%s> found", qPrint(tagName));
4860 children().append<DocWord>(parser(),thisVariant, "<"+tagName+parser()->context.token->attribsStr+">");
4861 break;
4862 case XML_INHERITDOC:
4863 handleInheritDoc(thisVariant);
4864 break;
4865 default:
4866 // we should not get here!
4867 ASSERT(0);
4868 break;
4869 }
4870 return retval;
4871}

4873int DocPara::handleHtmlEndTag(DocNodeVariant *thisVariant,const QCString &tagName)
4874{
4875 DBG(("handleHtmlEndTag(%s)\n",qPrint(tagName)));
4876 int tagId = Mappers::htmlTagMapper->map(tagName);

4881 if (!insideUL(thisVariant))
4882 {
4883 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"found </ul> tag without matching <ul>");
4884 }
4885 else
4886 {
4887 retval=RetVal_EndList;
4888 }
4889 break;
4890 case HTML_OL:
4891 if (!insideOL(thisVariant))
4892 {
4893 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"found </ol> tag without matching <ol>");
4894 }
4895 else
4896 {
4897 retval=RetVal_EndList;
4898 }
4899 break;
4900 case HTML_LI:
4901 if (!insideLI(thisVariant))
4902 {
4903 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"found </li> tag without matching <li>");
4904 }
4905 else
4906 {
4907 // ignore </li> tags
4908 }
4909 break;

4911 retval=RetVal_EndHtmlDetails;
4912 break;

4948 break;

4951 break;

4954 break;
4955 case HTML_SMALL:
4956 parser()->handleStyleLeave(thisVariant,children(),DocStyleChange::Small,tagName);
4957 break;

4959 parser()->handleStyleLeave(thisVariant,children(),DocStyleChange::Cite,tagName);
4960 break;

4965 break;
4966 case HTML_P:

4968 break;
4969 case HTML_DL:

4971 break;
4972 case HTML_DT:
4973 // ignore </dt> tag

4977 break;
4978 case HTML_TABLE:

4980 break;
4981 case HTML_TR:
4982 // ignore </tr> tag
4983 break;
4984 case HTML_TD:
4985 // ignore </td> tag
4986 break;
4987 case HTML_TH:

4989 break;

4992 break;

5069
5070int DocPara::parse(DocNodeVariant *thisVariant)
5071{
5072 DBG(("DocPara::parse() start\n"));
5073 auto ns = AutoNodeStack(parser(),thisVariant);
5074 // handle style commands "inherited" from the previous paragraph
5075 parser()->handleInitialStyleCommands(thisVariant,children());
5076 int tok;
5077 int retval=0;
5078 while ((tok=parser()->tokenizer.lex())) // get the next token
5079 {
5080reparsetoken:
5081 DBG(("token %s at %d",DocTokenizer::tokToString(tok),parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr()));
5082 if (tok==TK_WORD || tok==TK_LNKWORD || tok==TK_SYMBOL || tok==TK_URL ||
5083 tok==TK_COMMAND_AT || tok == TK_COMMAND_BS || tok==TK_HTMLTAG
5084 )
5085 {
5086 DBG((" name=%s",qPrint(parser()->context.token->name)));
5087 }
5088 DBG(("\n"));
5089 switch(tok)
5090 {
5091 case TK_WORD:
5092 children().append<DocWord>(parser(),thisVariant,parser()->context.token->name);
5093 break;
5094 case TK_LNKWORD:
5095 parser()->handleLinkedWord(thisVariant,children());
5096 break;
5097 case TK_URL:
5098 children().append<DocURL>(parser(),thisVariant,parser()->context.token->name,parser()->context.token->isEMailAddr);
5099 break;
5100 case TK_WHITESPACE:
5101 {
5102 // prevent leading whitespace and collapse multiple whitespace areas
5103 if (insidePRE(thisVariant) || // all whitespace is relevant
5104 (
5105 // remove leading whitespace
5106 !children().empty() &&
5107 // and whitespace after certain constructs
5108 !holds_one_of_alternatives<DocHtmlDescList, DocHtmlTable, DocHtmlList, DocSimpleSect,
5109 DocAutoList, DocSimpleList, DocHtmlHeader, DocHtmlBlockQuote,
5110 DocParamSect, DocHtmlDetails, DocXRefItem>(children().back())
5111 )
5112 )
5113 {
5114 children().append<DocWhiteSpace>(parser(),thisVariant,parser()->context.token->chars);
5115 }
5116 }
5117 break;
5118 case TK_LISTITEM:
5119 {
5120 DBG(("found list item at %d\n",parser()->context.token->indent));
5121 const DocNodeVariant *n=parent();
5122 while (n && !std::holds_alternative<DocAutoList>(*n)) n=::parent(n);
5123 const DocAutoList *al = std::get_if<DocAutoList>(n);
5124 if (al) // we found an auto list up in the hierarchy
5125 {
5126 DBG(("previous list item at %d\n",al->indent()));
5127 if (al->indent()>=parser()->context.token->indent)
5128 // new item at the same or lower indent level
5129 {
5130 retval=TK_LISTITEM;
5131 goto endparagraph;
5132 }
5133 }
5134
5135 // determine list depth
5136 int depth = 0;
5137 n=parent();
5138 while (n)
5139 {
5140 al = std::get_if<DocAutoList>(n);
5141 if (al && al->isEnumList()) depth++;
5142 n=::parent(n);
5143 }
5144
5145 // first item or sub list => create new list
5146 do
5147 {
5148 auto vDocAutoList = children().append<DocAutoList>(parser(),thisVariant,
5149 parser()->context.token->indent,
5150 parser()->context.token->isEnumList,depth);
5151 al = children().get_last<DocAutoList>();
5152 retval = children().get_last<DocAutoList>()->parse(vDocAutoList);
5153 } while (retval==TK_LISTITEM && // new list
5154 al->indent()==parser()->context.token->indent // at same indent level
5155 );
5156
5157 // check the return value
5158 if (retval==RetVal_SimpleSec) // auto list ended due to simple section command
5159 {
5160 // Reparse the token that ended the section at this level,
5161 // so a new simple section will be started at this level.
5162 // This is the same as unputting the last read token and continuing.
5163 parser()->context.token->name = parser()->context.token->simpleSectName;
5164 if (parser()->context.token->name.startsWith("rcs:")) // RCS section
5165 {
5166 parser()->context.token->name = parser()->context.token->name.mid(4);
5167 parser()->context.token->text = parser()->context.token->simpleSectText;
5168 tok = TK_RCSTAG;
5169 }
5170 else // other section
5171 {
5172 tok = TK_COMMAND_BS;
5173 }
5174 DBG(("reparsing command %s\n",qPrint(parser()->context.token->name)));
5175 goto reparsetoken;
5176 }
5177 else if (retval==TK_ENDLIST)
5178 {
5179 if (al->indent()>parser()->context.token->indent) // end list
5180 {
5181 goto endparagraph;
5182 }
5183 else // continue with current paragraph
5184 {
5185 }
5186 }
5187 else // paragraph ended due to TK_NEWPARA, TK_LISTITEM, or EOF
5188 {
5189 goto endparagraph;
5190 }
5191 }
5192 break;
5193 case TK_ENDLIST:
5194 DBG(("Found end of list inside of paragraph at line %d\n",parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr()));
5195 if (std::get_if<DocAutoListItem>(parent()))
5196 {
5197 const DocAutoList *al = std::get_if<DocAutoList>(::parent(parent()));
5198 if (al && al->indent()>=parser()->context.token->indent)
5199 {
5200 // end of list marker ends this paragraph
5201 retval=TK_ENDLIST;
5202 goto endparagraph;
5203 }
5204 else
5205 {
5206 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"End of list marker found "
5207 "has invalid indent level");
5208 }
5209 }
5210 else
5211 {
5212 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"End of list marker found without any preceding "
5213 "list items");
5214 }
5215 break;
5216 case TK_COMMAND_AT:
5217 // fall through
5218 case TK_COMMAND_BS:
5219 {
5220 // see if we have to start a simple section
5221 int cmd = Mappers::cmdMapper->map(parser()->context.token->name);
5222 const DocNodeVariant *n=parent();
5223 while (n && !std::holds_alternative<DocSimpleSect>(*n) &&
5224 !std::holds_alternative<DocParamSect>(*n))
5225 {
5226 n=::parent(n);
5227 }
5228 if (cmd&SIMPLESECT_BIT)
5229 {
5230 if (n) // already in a simple section
5231 {
5232 // simple section cannot start in this paragraph, need
5233 // to unwind the stack and remember the command.
5234 parser()->context.token->simpleSectName = parser()->context.token->name;
5235 retval=RetVal_SimpleSec;
5236 goto endparagraph;
5237 }
5238 }
5239 // see if we are in a simple list
5240 n=parent();
5241 while (n && !std::holds_alternative<DocSimpleListItem>(*n)) n=::parent(n);
5242 if (n)
5243 {
5244 if (cmd==CMD_LI)
5245 {
5246 retval=RetVal_ListItem;
5247 goto endparagraph;
5248 }
5249 }
5250
5251 // handle the command
5252 retval=handleCommand(thisVariant,parser()->context.token->name,tok);
5253 DBG(("handleCommand returns %s\n",DocTokenizer::retvalToString(retval)));
5254
5255 // check the return value
5256 if (retval==RetVal_SimpleSec)
5257 {
5258 // Reparse the token that ended the section at this level,
5259 // so a new simple section will be started at this level.
5260 // This is the same as unputting the last read token and continuing.
5261 parser()->context.token->name = parser()->context.token->simpleSectName;
5262 if (parser()->context.token->name.startsWith("rcs:")) // RCS section
5263 {
5264 parser()->context.token->name = parser()->context.token->name.mid(4);
5265 parser()->context.token->text = parser()->context.token->simpleSectText;
5266 tok = TK_RCSTAG;
5267 }
5268 else // other section
5269 {
5270 tok = TK_COMMAND_BS;
5271 }
5272 DBG(("reparsing command %s\n",qPrint(parser()->context.token->name)));
5273 goto reparsetoken;
5274 }
5275 else if (retval>0 && retval<RetVal_OK)
5276 {
5277 // the command ended with a new command, reparse this token
5278 tok = retval;
5279 goto reparsetoken;
5280 }
5281 else if (retval != RetVal_OK) // end of file, end of paragraph, start or end of section
5282 // or some auto list marker
5283 {
5284 goto endparagraph;
5285 }
5286 }
5287 break;
5288 case TK_HTMLTAG:
5289 {
5290 if (!parser()->context.token->endTag) // found a start tag
5291 {
5292 retval = handleHtmlStartTag(thisVariant,parser()->context.token->name,parser()->context.token->attribs);
5293 }
5294 else // found an end tag
5295 {
5296 retval = handleHtmlEndTag(thisVariant,parser()->context.token->name);
5297 }
5298 if (retval!=RetVal_OK)
5299 {
5300 goto endparagraph;
5301 }
5302 }
5303 break;
5304 case TK_SYMBOL:
5305 {
5306 HtmlEntityMapper::SymType s = DocSymbol::decodeSymbol(parser()->context.token->name);
5307 if (s!=HtmlEntityMapper::Sym_Unknown)
5308 {
5309 children().append<DocSymbol>(parser(),thisVariant,s);
5310 }
5311 else
5312 {
5313 children().append<DocWord>(parser(),thisVariant,parser()->context.token->name);
5314 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"Unsupported symbol %s found",
5315 qPrint(parser()->context.token->name));
5316 }
5317 break;
5318 }
5319 case TK_NEWPARA:
5320 retval=TK_NEWPARA;
5321 goto endparagraph;
5322 case TK_RCSTAG:
5323 {
5324 const DocNodeVariant *n=parent();
5325 while (n && !std::holds_alternative<DocSimpleSect>(*n) &&
5326 !std::holds_alternative<DocParamSect>(*n))
5327 {
5328 n=::parent(n);
5329 }
5330 if (n) // already in a simple section
5331 {
5332 // simple section cannot start in this paragraph, need
5333 // to unwind the stack and remember the command.
5334 parser()->context.token->simpleSectName = "rcs:"+parser()->context.token->name;
5335 parser()->context.token->simpleSectText = parser()->context.token->text;
5336 retval=RetVal_SimpleSec;
5337 goto endparagraph;
5338 }
5339
5340 // see if we are in a simple list
5341 auto vDocSimpleSect = children().append<DocSimpleSect>(parser(),thisVariant,DocSimpleSect::Rcs);
5342 children().get_last<DocSimpleSect>()->parseRcs(vDocSimpleSect);
5343 }
5344 break;
5345 default:
5346 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),
5347 "Found unexpected token (id=%s)\n",DocTokenizer::tokToString(tok));
5348 break;
5349 }
5350 }
5351 retval=0;
5352endparagraph:
5353 parser()->handlePendingStyleCommands(thisVariant,children());
5354 DBG(("DocPara::parse() end retval=%s\n",DocTokenizer::retvalToString(retval)));
5355 DocPara *par = std::get_if<DocPara>(parser()->context.nodeStack.top());
5356 if (!parser()->context.token->endTag && par &&
5357 retval==TK_NEWPARA && parser()->context.token->name.lower() == "p")
5358 {
5359 par->setAttribs(parser()->context.token->attribs);
5360 }
5361 INTERNAL_ASSERT(retval==0 || retval==TK_NEWPARA || retval==TK_LISTITEM ||
5362 retval==TK_ENDLIST || retval>RetVal_OK
5363 );
5364
5365 return retval;
5366}

5368//--------------------------------------------------------------------------
5369
5370int DocSection::parse(DocNodeVariant *thisVariant)
5371{
5372 DBG(("DocSection::parse() start %s level=%d\n",qPrint(parser()->context.token->sectionId),m_level));
5373 int retval=RetVal_OK;
5374 auto ns = AutoNodeStack(parser(),thisVariant);
5375
5376 if (!m_id.isEmpty())
5377 {
5378 const SectionInfo *sec = SectionManager::instance().find(m_id);
5379 if (sec)
5380 {
5381 m_file = sec->fileName();
5382 m_anchor = sec->label();
5383 m_title = sec->title();
5384 if (m_title.isEmpty()) m_title = sec->label();
5385 }
5386 }
5387
5388 // first parse any number of paragraphs
5389 bool isFirst=TRUE;
5390 DocPara *lastPar=0;
5391 do
5392 {
5393 auto vDocPara = children().append<DocPara>(parser(),thisVariant);
5394 DocPara *par = children().get_last<DocPara>();
5395 if (isFirst) { par->markFirst(); isFirst=FALSE; }
5396 retval=par->parse(vDocPara);
5397 if (!par->isEmpty())
5398 {
5399 if (lastPar) lastPar->markLast(FALSE);
5400 lastPar = par;
5401 }
5402 else
5403 {
5404 children().pop_back();
5405 }
5406 if (retval==TK_LISTITEM)
5407 {
5408 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"Invalid list item found");
5409 }
5410 if (retval==RetVal_Internal)
5411 {
5412 auto vDocInternal = children().append<DocInternal>(parser(),thisVariant);
5413 retval = children().get_last<DocInternal>()->parse(vDocInternal,m_level+1);
5414 if (retval==RetVal_EndInternal)
5415 {
5416 retval=RetVal_OK;
5417 }
5418 }
5419 } while (retval!=0 &&
5420 retval!=RetVal_Section &&
5421 retval!=RetVal_Subsection &&
5422 retval!=RetVal_Subsubsection &&
5423 retval!=RetVal_Paragraph &&
5424 retval!=RetVal_EndInternal
5425 );
5426
5427 if (lastPar) lastPar->markLast();
5428
5429 //printf("m_level=%d <-> %d\n",m_level,Doxygen::subpageNestingLevel);
5430
5431 while (true)
5432 {
5433 if (retval==RetVal_Subsection && m_level<=Doxygen::subpageNestingLevel+1)
5434 {
5435 // then parse any number of nested sections
5436 while (retval==RetVal_Subsection) // more sections follow
5437 {
5438 auto vDocSection = children().append<DocSection>(parser(),thisVariant,
5439 std::min(2+Doxygen::subpageNestingLevel,5),
5440 parser()->context.token->sectionId);
5441 retval = children().get_last<DocSection>()->parse(vDocSection);
5442 }
5443 break;
5444 }
5445 else if (retval==RetVal_Subsubsection && m_level<=Doxygen::subpageNestingLevel+2)
5446 {
5447 if ((m_level<=1+Doxygen::subpageNestingLevel) && !parser()->context.token->sectionId.startsWith("autotoc_md"))
5448 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"Unexpected subsubsection command found inside %s!",g_sectionLevelToName[m_level]);
5449 // then parse any number of nested sections
5450 while (retval==RetVal_Subsubsection) // more sections follow
5451 {
5452 auto vDocSection = children().append<DocSection>(parser(),thisVariant,
5453 std::min(3+Doxygen::subpageNestingLevel,5),
5454 parser()->context.token->sectionId);
5455 retval = children().get_last<DocSection>()->parse(vDocSection);
5456 }
5457 if (!(m_level<Doxygen::subpageNestingLevel+2 && retval == RetVal_Subsection)) break;
5458 }
5459 else if (retval==RetVal_Paragraph && m_level<=std::min(5,Doxygen::subpageNestingLevel+3))
5460 {
5461 if ((m_level<=2+Doxygen::subpageNestingLevel) && !parser()->context.token->sectionId.startsWith("autotoc_md"))
5462 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"Unexpected paragraph command found inside %s!",g_sectionLevelToName[m_level]);
5463 // then parse any number of nested sections
5464 while (retval==RetVal_Paragraph) // more sections follow
5465 {
5466 auto vDocSection = children().append<DocSection>(parser(),thisVariant,
5467 std::min(4+Doxygen::subpageNestingLevel,5),
5468 parser()->context.token->sectionId);
5469 retval = children().get_last<DocSection>()->parse(vDocSection);
5470 }
5471 if (!(m_level<Doxygen::subpageNestingLevel+3 && (retval == RetVal_Subsection || retval == RetVal_Subsubsection))) break;
5472 }
5473 else
5474 {
5475 break;
5476 }
5477 }
5478
5479 INTERNAL_ASSERT(retval==0 ||
5480 retval==RetVal_Section ||
5481 retval==RetVal_Subsection ||
5482 retval==RetVal_Subsubsection ||
5483 retval==RetVal_Paragraph ||
5484 retval==RetVal_Internal ||
5485 retval==RetVal_EndInternal
5486 );
5487
5488 DBG(("DocSection::parse() end: retval=%s\n",DocTokenizer::retvalToString(retval)));
5489 return retval;
5490}
